1
00:00:53,866 --> 00:00:56,911
WEATHERMAN [ON RADIO]: I don't know
about you, it's too hot today, isn't it?

2
00:00:57,078 --> 00:01:01,249
And it's going to get even worse.
Temperatures up in the mid-30s Celsius...

3
00:01:01,415 --> 00:01:05,127
...that's the mid-90s Fahrenheit,
tomorrow, maybe even hitting 100.

4
00:01:05,294 --> 00:01:07,964
So, please, remember to cover up
and stay cool...

5
00:01:08,130 --> 00:01:10,967
...with the hottest hits on your FM dial.

6
00:01:11,133 --> 00:01:13,886
WOMAN:
Come on, guys, time to go home.

7
00:01:14,637 --> 00:01:16,806
Come on, love, off you get.

8
00:01:18,724 --> 00:01:22,144
CHILD: Do we have to?
WOMAN: Yes, we do.

9
00:01:22,812 --> 00:01:25,690
I'll make you your favorite dinner
to compensate.

10
00:01:25,856 --> 00:01:26,899
[BOYS LAUGHING]

11
00:01:27,066 --> 00:01:28,734
MALCOLM:
He squealed like a pig, didn't he?

12
00:01:28,901 --> 00:01:32,446
PIERS: Yeah, brilliant punch, Big D.
Did you see his face?

13
00:01:32,613 --> 00:01:34,448
HARRY:
Hey, Big D.

14
00:01:35,324 --> 00:01:36,951
Beat up another 10-year-old?

15
00:01:37,118 --> 00:01:39,620
-This one deserved it.
GANG: Yeah.

16
00:01:40,204 --> 00:01:44,458
HARRY: Five against one, very brave.
-Well, you're one to talk.

17
00:01:44,625 --> 00:01:48,629
Moaning in your sleep every night?
At least I'm not afraid of my pillow.

18
00:01:48,838 --> 00:01:51,340
[GANG LAUGHING]

19
00:01:52,049 --> 00:01:54,885
DUDLEY:
"Don't kill Cedric."”

20
00:01:55,344 --> 00:01:56,971
Who's Cedric, your boyfriend?

21
00:01:58,347 --> 00:02:02,351
-Shut up.
DUDLEY: "He's going to kill me, Mum."

22
00:02:02,727 --> 00:02:04,979
Where is your mum?

23
00:02:05,855 --> 00:02:08,441
Where is your mum, Potter?

24
00:02:08,899 --> 00:02:10,067
She dead?

25
00:02:10,234 --> 00:02:11,652
[GANG LAUGHS AND GROANS]

26
00:02:11,861 --> 00:02:13,487
Is she dead?

27
00:02:13,988 --> 00:02:15,323
Is she a dead Pott--?

28
00:02:15,489 --> 00:02:16,949
GANG:
Whoa.

29
00:02:17,366 --> 00:02:19,493
[GANG LAUGHING]

30
00:02:19,660 --> 00:02:21,412
[WIND BLOWING]

31
00:02:29,545 --> 00:02:31,380
BOY 1: Dudley.
BOY 2: Dudley, let's go.

32
00:02:34,258 --> 00:02:36,093
-What's going on?
-What are you doing?

33
00:02:36,260 --> 00:02:39,221
-I'm not doing anything.
BOY 3: We're getting out of here, Dudley.

34
00:02:39,388 --> 00:02:40,931
BOY 4:
Come on, Dudley, hurry up.

35
00:02:48,981 --> 00:02:51,776
[HARRY AND DUDLEY PANTING]

36
00:03:28,229 --> 00:03:30,940
[HARRY GRUNTING]

37
00:03:31,273 --> 00:03:33,234
HARRY:
Dudley, run.

38
00:03:36,028 --> 00:03:37,696
[DUDLEY GRUNTS AND YELLS]

39
00:03:42,034 --> 00:03:43,786
[HARRY CHOKING]

40
00:03:54,547 --> 00:03:56,215
[DUDLEY GROANING]

41
00:04:08,894 --> 00:04:10,271
Expecto Patronum.

42
00:04:18,487 --> 00:04:20,322
[DUDLEY GRUNTING]

43
00:04:29,540 --> 00:04:31,500
[HARRY PANTING]

44
00:04:40,134 --> 00:04:41,927
Mrs. Figg.

45
00:04:45,806 --> 00:04:47,892
Don't put away your wand, Harry.

46
00:04:48,184 --> 00:04:50,561
They might come back.

47
00:04:51,854 --> 00:04:54,815
FIGG: Dementors in Little Whinging,
whatever next?

48
00:04:55,024 --> 00:04:58,944
-Whole world's gone topsy-turvy.
- I don't understand. How do you know--?

49
00:04:59,111 --> 00:05:01,322
Dumbledore asked me
to keep an eye on you.

50
00:05:01,530 --> 00:05:03,574
Dumbledore asked you?
You know Dumbledore?

51
00:05:03,741 --> 00:05:04,867
FIGG:
Uh-huh.

52
00:05:05,034 --> 00:05:08,871
After You-Know-Who
killed that poor Diggory boy last year...

53
00:05:09,038 --> 00:05:11,707
...did you expect him to let you
go wandering on your own?

54
00:05:11,874 --> 00:05:14,543
Good Lord, boy.
They told me you were intelligent.

55
00:05:14,710 --> 00:05:17,838
Now, get inside and stay there.

56
00:05:18,047 --> 00:05:19,632
Expect someone will be in touch soon.

57
00:05:19,798 --> 00:05:22,676
[WHISPERING]
Whatever happens, don't leave the house.

58
00:05:32,102 --> 00:05:34,480
WEATHERMAN:
It is hot. That's right, hot everywhere.

59
00:05:34,647 --> 00:05:36,774
There's sweat. There's stifling.

60
00:05:36,941 --> 00:05:38,859
Diddykins?

61
00:05:39,193 --> 00:05:41,195
Is that you?

62
00:05:44,406 --> 00:05:47,576
Duddy. Vernon, come quick.

63
00:05:48,327 --> 00:05:50,746
We're going to have to
take him to a hospital.

64
00:05:50,913 --> 00:05:53,082
Who did this to you, boy?

65
00:05:57,461 --> 00:06:00,381
Happy, are we, now? Eh?

66
00:06:00,589 --> 00:06:03,217
You've finally done it.
You've finally driven him loopy.

67
00:06:03,384 --> 00:06:06,220
[WHISPERING]
Vernon, don't say that.

68
00:06:06,387 --> 00:06:10,724
VERNON: Well, just look at him, Petunia.
Our boy has gone yumpy.

69
00:06:11,100 --> 00:06:13,060
I've reached my limit, do you hear?

70
00:06:13,227 --> 00:06:17,106
This is the last I'm gonna take
of you and your nonsense.

71
00:06:18,148 --> 00:06:20,150
[OWL SCREECHES]
[THUD]

72
00:06:20,901 --> 00:06:22,736
[VERNON WHIMPERING]

73
00:06:26,115 --> 00:06:28,117
[OWL WHINING]

74
00:06:30,995 --> 00:06:33,080
-Dear Mr. Potter.
VERNON [WHISPERING]: What?

75
00:06:33,247 --> 00:06:38,502
The Ministry has received intelligence
that at 6:23 this evening...

76
00:06:38,669 --> 00:06:43,424
...you performed the Patronus Charm
in the presence of a Muggle.

77
00:06:43,632 --> 00:06:45,676
As a clear violation...

78
00:06:45,843 --> 00:06:49,930
...of the Decree for the Reasonable
Restriction of Underage Sorcery...

79
00:06:50,139 --> 00:06:52,224
...you are hereby expelled...

80
00:06:52,641 --> 00:06:56,145
...from Hogwarts School
of Witchcraft and Wizardry.

81
00:06:56,812 --> 00:07:01,233
Hoping you are well, Mafalda Hopkirk.

82
00:07:05,362 --> 00:07:07,698
Justice.

83
00:07:07,865 --> 00:07:10,451
[DUDLEY WHIMPERING
AND MUTTERING]

84
00:07:19,960 --> 00:07:22,171
[WHISPERING]
He's not very well.

85
00:07:23,464 --> 00:07:25,174
[HARRY GRUNTS]
[HEDWIG SCREECHES]

86
00:07:34,683 --> 00:07:36,477
Sorry, Hedwig.

87
00:08:12,805 --> 00:08:15,224
[CLATTERING]

88
00:08:42,376 --> 00:08:43,544
[HEDWIG SCREECHES]

89
00:08:43,752 --> 00:08:45,504
WOMAN [WHISPERING]:
Very clean, these Muggles.

90
00:08:45,838 --> 00:08:48,757
MOODY: Tonks, for God's sake.
TONKS: Unnatural.

91
00:08:52,678 --> 00:08:54,263
Professor Moody.

92
00:08:54,680 --> 00:08:57,766
-What are you doing here?
-Rescuing you, of course.

93
00:09:00,602 --> 00:09:03,313
But where are we going?
The letter said I've been expelled.

94
00:09:03,480 --> 00:09:05,899
You haven't been. Not yet.
Kingsley, you take point.

95
00:09:06,066 --> 00:09:08,652
-But the letter said--
-Dumbledore persuaded the minister...

96
00:09:08,819 --> 00:09:11,238
...10 suspend your expulsion,
pending a formal hearing.

97
00:09:11,405 --> 00:09:12,614
-A hearing?
SHACKLEBOLT: Uh-huh.

98
00:09:12,781 --> 00:09:15,701
Don't worry. We'll explain everything
when we get back to headquarters.

99
00:09:15,868 --> 00:09:18,620
Shh! Not here, Nymphadora.

100
00:09:18,787 --> 00:09:22,624
Don't call me Nymphadora.

101
00:09:27,963 --> 00:09:32,092
Stay in formation, everyone.
Don't break ranks if one of us is killed.

102
00:09:32,509 --> 00:09:34,094
[WHOOSHING]

103
00:10:21,850 --> 00:10:23,936
MAN:
Come on, you, around the corner.

104
00:10:25,979 --> 00:10:27,439
MOODY:
Come on.

105
00:10:38,033 --> 00:10:39,952
[WIND CHIMES CLINKING]

106
00:10:40,160 --> 00:10:41,870
[RUMBLING]

107
00:10:53,590 --> 00:10:55,676
[LAUGHTER ON TV]

108
00:11:06,895 --> 00:11:08,647
In you go, son.

109
00:11:10,190 --> 00:11:11,692
ARTHUR:
There've been no sightings.

110
00:11:11,900 --> 00:11:13,569
No deaths. No proof.

111
00:11:13,735 --> 00:11:16,613
SIRIUS: He almost killed Harry.
If that isn't proof enough...

112
00:11:16,780 --> 00:11:20,701
ARTHUR: Yes, but guarding
you-know-what is the most important...

113
00:11:21,326 --> 00:11:22,828
[MOODY GRUNTS]

114
00:11:22,995 --> 00:11:25,414
ARTHUR:
We must trust Dumbledore on this.

115
00:11:25,581 --> 00:11:27,708
SIRIUS:
Was he able to protect Harry last year?

116
00:11:27,916 --> 00:11:29,960
Well, tonight I say
it's time to take action.

117
00:11:30,127 --> 00:11:31,169
TONKS:
Ooh!

118
00:11:31,336 --> 00:11:33,380
ARTHUR: Cornelius Fudge is a politician
first and a wizard second.

119
00:11:33,547 --> 00:11:36,717
-His instinct would be to ignore it--
MOLLY: Shh. Keep your voices down.

120
00:11:36,925 --> 00:11:41,305
He's getting stronger and stronger
by the minute. We have to act now.

121
00:11:45,267 --> 00:11:47,561
-Harry.
-Mrs. Weasley.

122
00:11:50,230 --> 00:11:52,149
Heavens, you're all right.

123
00:11:52,316 --> 00:11:53,609
[MOLLY CHUCKLES]

124
00:11:56,236 --> 00:11:59,948
Bit peaky, but I'm afraid dinner will wait
until after the meeting's finished.

125
00:12:00,115 --> 00:12:05,245
Nope. No time to explain.
Straight upstairs, first door on the left.

126
00:12:05,621 --> 00:12:07,080
Yeah.

127
00:12:09,333 --> 00:12:14,546
VOICE:
Mudblood, werewolves, traitors, thieves.

128
00:12:14,713 --> 00:12:19,593
If my poor mistress
knew the scum they let into her house...

129
00:12:19,760 --> 00:12:22,054
...what would she say to old Kreacher?

130
00:12:23,096 --> 00:12:26,099
Oh, the shame.

131
00:12:38,487 --> 00:12:41,198
WOMAN'S VOICE: Freaks.
KREACHER: There, there, mistress.

132
00:12:41,490 --> 00:12:44,785
WOMAN'S VOICE: Scum of the earth.
Not like it was in the days of my fathers.

133
00:12:44,993 --> 00:12:47,579
KREACHER:
Kreacher is here.

134
00:12:51,625 --> 00:12:53,085
Oh, Harry.

135
00:12:55,879 --> 00:12:59,716
Are you all right? We overheard them
talking about the Dementor attack.

136
00:12:59,883 --> 00:13:02,719
-You must tell us everything.
-Let the man breathe, Hermione.

137
00:13:02,886 --> 00:13:07,099
And this hearing at the Ministry.
It's just outrageous.

138
00:13:07,265 --> 00:13:09,434
I've looked it up.
They simply can't expel you.

139
00:13:09,601 --> 00:13:12,312
-It's completely unfair.
-Yeah.

140
00:13:12,813 --> 00:13:15,440
There's a lot of that
going round at the moment.

141
00:13:17,317 --> 00:13:19,277
So, what is this place?

142
00:13:19,444 --> 00:13:22,155
-It's headquarters.
-Of the Order of the Phoenix.

143
00:13:22,948 --> 00:13:24,449
It's a secret society.

144
00:13:24,616 --> 00:13:27,160
Dumbledore formed it back when
they fought You-Know-Who.

145
00:13:27,327 --> 00:13:29,913
Couldn't have put any of this
in a letter, I suppose?

146
00:13:30,580 --> 00:13:32,791
I've gone all summer
without a scrap of news.

147
00:13:33,375 --> 00:13:37,004
We wanted to write, mate.
Really, we did.

148
00:13:37,170 --> 00:13:38,213
-Only...
-Only what?

149
00:13:38,380 --> 00:13:41,591
Only Dumbledore made us swear
not to tell you anything.

150
00:13:43,385 --> 00:13:45,095
Dumbledore said that?

151
00:13:46,888 --> 00:13:49,641
But why would he keep me in the dark?
Maybe I could help.

152
00:13:49,808 --> 00:13:51,768
I'm the one who saw Voldemort return...

153
00:13:51,935 --> 00:13:54,771
...the one who fought him,
who saw Cedric Diggory get killed.

154
00:13:54,938 --> 00:13:57,149
FRED: Harry.
-Thought we heard your dulcet tones.

155
00:13:57,315 --> 00:13:59,693
FRED: Don't bottle it up,
though, mate. Let it out.

156
00:13:59,860 --> 00:14:01,361
If you're all done shouting...

157
00:14:01,570 --> 00:14:04,072
Do you wanna hear something
a little more interesting?

158
00:14:05,282 --> 00:14:07,826
SIRIUS [OVER SPEAKER]:
If anyone has a right to know, it's Harry.

159
00:14:07,993 --> 00:14:10,912
If it wasn't for Harry, we wouldn't
even know Voldemort was back.

160
00:14:11,079 --> 00:14:12,664
He's not a child, Molly.

161
00:14:12,831 --> 00:14:15,208
MOLLY:
But he's not an adult either.

162
00:14:15,500 --> 00:14:18,420
-He's not James, Sirius.
SIRIUS: Well, he's not your son.

163
00:14:18,587 --> 00:14:20,756
MOLLY:
He's as good as.

164
00:14:21,131 --> 00:14:22,841
-Who else has he got?
HARRY: Hey, Ginny.

165
00:14:23,008 --> 00:14:25,427
SIRIUS: He's got me.
SNAPE: How touchingly paternal, Black.

166
00:14:25,594 --> 00:14:28,722
Perhaps Potter will grow up to be a felon,
just like his godfather.

167
00:14:28,889 --> 00:14:30,640
SIRIUS:
Now, you stay out of this, Snivellus.

168
00:14:30,807 --> 00:14:32,726
-Snape's part of the Order?
-Git.

169
00:14:32,893 --> 00:14:34,352
SIRIUS:
--about your supposed reformation.

170
00:14:34,519 --> 00:14:35,562
[MEOWS]

171
00:14:35,729 --> 00:14:37,814
- Know better.
SNAPE: So why don't you tell him?

172
00:14:37,981 --> 00:14:39,691
FRED: Get off it.
GEORGE: Quick.

173
00:14:39,858 --> 00:14:41,485
-Get it up.
-Crookshanks.

174
00:14:41,902 --> 00:14:44,071
-Stop it.
FRED: Get off, you bloody cat.

175
00:14:44,237 --> 00:14:46,490
-Crookshanks. Leave it alone.
-Get it up.

176
00:14:48,450 --> 00:14:51,078
RON: Hermione, I hate your cat.
-Bad Crookshanks.

177
00:14:51,244 --> 00:14:52,996
[RON LAUGHS]

178
00:14:53,371 --> 00:14:55,916
Well, we'll be eating down in the kitchen.

179
00:14:56,124 --> 00:14:57,125
Oh!

180
00:14:57,292 --> 00:14:59,294
Just because you're allowed
to use magic now...

181
00:14:59,461 --> 00:15:02,506
...does not mean you have to
whip your wands out for everything.

182
00:15:02,672 --> 00:15:04,257
GINNY:
Hi, Mum.

183
00:15:05,258 --> 00:15:06,968
You hungry, Harry?

184
00:15:07,135 --> 00:15:09,763
You sure you're all right, Harry?
Gave us quite a turn.

185
00:15:09,930 --> 00:15:12,140
SIRIUS:
Harry Potter.

186
00:15:14,309 --> 00:15:16,269
Sirius.

187
00:15:16,436 --> 00:15:18,021
[SIRIUS CHUCKLES]

188
00:15:18,480 --> 00:15:19,648
SIRIUS:
Ohh.

189
00:15:20,273 --> 00:15:21,817
[HERMIONE AND GINNY LAUGHING]

190
00:15:21,983 --> 00:15:23,401
ARTHUR:
This is very, very peculiar.

191
00:15:23,568 --> 00:15:24,611
[TONKS SNORTING]

192
00:15:24,778 --> 00:15:28,073
It seems your hearing at the Ministry
is to be before the entire Wizengamot.

193
00:15:28,240 --> 00:15:31,576
I don't understand. What has
the Ministry of Magic got against me?

194
00:15:32,494 --> 00:15:35,914
Show him. He'll find out soon enough.

195
00:15:46,299 --> 00:15:49,302
SIRIUS:
He's been attacking Dumbledore as well.

196
00:15:51,179 --> 00:15:56,184
Fudge is using all his power, including
his influence at the Daily Prophet...

197
00:15:56,476 --> 00:15:59,479
...to smear anyone who claims
the Dark Lord has returned.

198
00:15:59,688 --> 00:16:00,939
HARRY:
Why?

199
00:16:01,106 --> 00:16:03,066
He thinks Dumbledore's after his job.

200
00:16:03,233 --> 00:16:05,360
No one in their right mind
could believe that--

201
00:16:05,527 --> 00:16:08,405
Exactly the point.
Fudge isn't in his right mind.

202
00:16:08,572 --> 00:16:11,116
It's been twisted and warped by fear.

203
00:16:12,784 --> 00:16:15,203
Now, fear makes people
do terrible things, Harry.

204
00:16:15,370 --> 00:16:17,831
The last time Voldemort gained power...

205
00:16:17,998 --> 00:16:21,334
...he almost destroyed
everything we hold most dear.

206
00:16:21,501 --> 00:16:25,422
Now he's returned, and I'm afraid
the minister will do almost anything...

207
00:16:25,589 --> 00:16:28,508
...to avoid facing that terrifying truth.

208
00:16:29,801 --> 00:16:34,472
We think Voldemort
wants to build up his army again.

209
00:16:35,599 --> 00:16:38,268
Fourteen years ago,
he had huge numbers at his command.

210
00:16:38,435 --> 00:16:43,023
And not just witches and wizards,
but all manner of dark creatures.

211
00:16:43,607 --> 00:16:47,652
He's been recruiting heavily, and
we've been attempting to do the same.

212
00:16:48,570 --> 00:16:52,365
But gathering followers
isn't the only thing he's interested in.

213
00:16:52,532 --> 00:16:53,825
[MOODY CLEARS THROAT]

214
00:16:55,285 --> 00:16:57,120
We believe...

215
00:16:58,079 --> 00:17:00,040
...Voldemort may be after something.

216
00:17:00,248 --> 00:17:01,333
Sirius.

217
00:17:04,961 --> 00:17:07,839
Something he didn't have last time.

218
00:17:09,299 --> 00:17:11,343
You mean like a weapon?

219
00:17:11,509 --> 00:17:15,555
No. That's enough. He's just a boy.

220
00:17:15,764 --> 00:17:18,558
You say more and you might as well
induct him into the Order.

221
00:17:18,767 --> 00:17:22,520
Good. I want to join. If Voldemort's
raising an army, then I want to fight.

222
00:17:27,025 --> 00:17:28,902
[SNORING]

223
00:17:34,991 --> 00:17:36,868
VOLDEMORT:
Harry.

224
00:17:37,035 --> 00:17:39,287
HOPKIRK:
You are hereby expelled.

225
00:17:39,454 --> 00:17:42,290
ARTHUR:
Before the entire Wizengamot.

226
00:17:43,208 --> 00:17:45,085
[TRAINS SCREECHING]

227
00:17:51,591 --> 00:17:53,385
ARTHUR:
Trains. Underground.

228
00:17:53,551 --> 00:17:55,845
Ingenious, these Muggles.

229
00:18:08,066 --> 00:18:09,484
Ahh.

230
00:18:13,029 --> 00:18:14,864
ARTHUR:
Here we are.

231
00:18:16,658 --> 00:18:21,121
I've never used the visitors' entrance
before. Should be fun.

232
00:18:21,830 --> 00:18:26,167
Right. Good.
I'll just get my Muggle money.

233
00:18:39,139 --> 00:18:40,390
[DINGS]

234
00:19:06,166 --> 00:19:09,085
Terrible. Lost a lot of Galleons
trading on the potions market.

235
00:19:09,252 --> 00:19:12,547
MAN: Daily Prophet, ladies and
gentlemen. Anybody for Daily Prophet?

236
00:19:12,714 --> 00:19:15,717
Dumbledore: Is he daft,
or is he dangerous?

237
00:19:37,697 --> 00:19:40,492
-Morning, Arthur.
-Morning, Bob.

238
00:19:43,119 --> 00:19:44,704
Interdepartmental memos.

239
00:19:44,913 --> 00:19:48,541
We used to use owls.
Mess was unbelievable.

240
00:19:48,708 --> 00:19:50,543
[SHACKLEBOLT PANTING]

241
00:19:51,336 --> 00:19:53,505
[WHISPERING INDISTINCTLY]

242
00:19:53,963 --> 00:19:57,384
Merlin's beard. Thank you, Kingsley.

243
00:19:57,550 --> 00:20:00,929
-They changed the time of your hearing.
-When is it?

244
00:20:01,346 --> 00:20:03,223
ARTHUR:
In five minutes.

245
00:20:10,939 --> 00:20:14,109
WOMAN'S VOICE:
Department of Mysteries.

246
00:20:16,653 --> 00:20:20,782
And I'm confident, minister,
that you will do the right thing.

247
00:20:20,949 --> 00:20:23,076
Yes, but we must be--

248
00:20:30,208 --> 00:20:33,628
Remember, during the hearing,
speak only when you're spoken to.

249
00:20:33,795 --> 00:20:37,340
Keep calm. You've done nothing wrong.

250
00:20:37,632 --> 00:20:40,969
As the Muggles say, truth will out.

251
00:20:41,469 --> 00:20:43,054
-Yes?

252
00:20:43,972 --> 00:20:46,266
I'm not allowed in, I'm afraid.

253
00:20:47,892 --> 00:20:49,644
Good luck, Harry.

254
00:20:52,355 --> 00:20:53,440
[GAVEL POUNDING]

255
00:20:53,606 --> 00:20:56,109
Disciplinary hearing
of the 12th of August...

256
00:20:56,276 --> 00:20:59,237
...into offenses committed
by Harry James Potter...

257
00:20:59,404 --> 00:21:03,032
...resident at Number 4 Privet Drive,
Little Whinging, Surrey.

258
00:21:03,199 --> 00:21:06,286
Interrogators: Cornelius Oswald Fudge,
Minister of Mag--

259
00:21:06,494 --> 00:21:08,288
DUMBLEDORE:
Witness for the defense.

260
00:21:08,496 --> 00:21:11,624
Albus Percival Wulfric...

261
00:21:12,000 --> 00:21:15,378
...Brian Dumbledore.

262
00:21:15,670 --> 00:21:18,965
You got our message
that the time and place of the hearing...

263
00:21:19,132 --> 00:21:21,676
-...had been changed, did you?
-I must have missed it.

264
00:21:21,843 --> 00:21:25,805
But by a happy mistake,
I arrived at the Ministry three hours early.

265
00:21:28,766 --> 00:21:29,976
The charges?

266
00:21:30,143 --> 00:21:32,645
The charges against the accused
are as follows:

267
00:21:32,812 --> 00:21:34,481
"That he did knowingly...

268
00:21:34,647 --> 00:21:38,193
...and in full awareness
of the illegality of his actions...

269
00:21:38,359 --> 00:21:41,362
...produce a Patronus Charm...

270
00:21:41,529 --> 00:21:44,782
...in the presence of a Muggle.”

271
00:21:44,949 --> 00:21:48,244
-Do you deny producing said Patronus?
-No, but--

272
00:21:48,411 --> 00:21:51,873
And you were aware that you were
forbidden to use magic outside school...

273
00:21:52,040 --> 00:21:54,918
-...while under the age of 17?
-Yes, I was, but--

274
00:21:55,084 --> 00:21:58,463
Witches and wizards of the Wizengamot--

275
00:21:58,630 --> 00:22:00,840
I was only doing it
because of the Dementors.

276
00:22:01,049 --> 00:22:02,884
[MURMURING]

277
00:22:03,593 --> 00:22:05,220
BONES:
Dementors?

278
00:22:05,845 --> 00:22:07,514
In Little Whinging?

279
00:22:07,680 --> 00:22:10,016
That's quite clever.

280
00:22:10,183 --> 00:22:13,353
Muggles can't see Dementors,
can they, boy?

281
00:22:13,603 --> 00:22:15,730
-Highly convenient.
-I'm not lying.

282
00:22:15,897 --> 00:22:18,483
-There were two of them, and if I hadn't--
-Enough.

283
00:22:18,650 --> 00:22:22,862
I'm sorry to interrupt what I'm sure would
have been a very well-rehearsed story...

284
00:22:23,071 --> 00:22:27,534
...but since you can produce
no witnesses of the event--

285
00:22:27,700 --> 00:22:32,288
Pardon me, minister,
but as it happens, we can.

286
00:22:35,625 --> 00:22:38,711
BONES:
Please describe the attack.

287
00:22:41,506 --> 00:22:43,299
What did they look like?

288
00:22:43,883 --> 00:22:49,305
Well, one of them was very large
and the other rather skinny.

289
00:22:50,390 --> 00:22:53,226
Not the boys. The Dementors.

290
00:22:53,393 --> 00:22:57,105
Oh, right, right. Well, um, big.

291
00:22:58,231 --> 00:23:02,860
Cloaked. Then everything went cold...

292
00:23:03,486 --> 00:23:06,906
...as though all the happiness
had gone from the world.

293
00:23:07,115 --> 00:23:12,161
Now, look here. Dementors don't just
wander into a Muggle suburb...

294
00:23:12,328 --> 00:23:15,957
...and happen across a wizard.
The odds are astronomical.

295
00:23:16,124 --> 00:23:17,875
DUMBLEDORE:
I don't think anyone would believe...

296
00:23:18,042 --> 00:23:20,420
...the Dementors were there
by coincidence, minister.

297
00:23:20,628 --> 00:23:22,213
[WOMAN CLEARS THROAT]

298
00:23:23,631 --> 00:23:26,467
I'm sure I must have misunderstood you,
professor.

299
00:23:26,634 --> 00:23:32,140
Dementors are, after all, under
the control of the Ministry of Magic.

300
00:23:32,307 --> 00:23:36,519
And it's so silly of me,
but it sounded for a moment as though...

301
00:23:36,686 --> 00:23:40,690
...you were suggesting that the Ministry
had ordered the attack on this boy.

302
00:23:40,857 --> 00:23:44,110
DUMBLEDORE: That would be disturbing
indeed, Madam Undersecretary...

303
00:23:44,277 --> 00:23:47,989
...which is why I'm sure the Ministry
will be mounting a full-scale inquiry...

304
00:23:48,156 --> 00:23:51,534
...into why the two Dementors
were so very far from Azkaban...

305
00:23:51,701 --> 00:23:55,079
...and why they mounted an attack
without authorization.

306
00:23:55,955 --> 00:23:58,166
Of course, there is someone...

307
00:23:58,499 --> 00:24:01,169
...who might be behind the attack.

308
00:24:04,172 --> 00:24:08,760
Cornelius, I implore you to see reason.

309
00:24:08,926 --> 00:24:13,473
The evidence that the Dark Lord
has returned is incontrovertible.

310
00:24:13,681 --> 00:24:16,434
[WHISPERING]
He is not back.

311
00:24:22,315 --> 00:24:24,525
DUMBLEDORE:
In the matter of Harry Potter...

312
00:24:25,109 --> 00:24:27,528
...the law clearly states...

313
00:24:27,779 --> 00:24:32,158
...that magic may be used before Muggles
in life-threatening situations.

314
00:24:32,325 --> 00:24:35,244
Laws can be changed if necessary,
Dumbledore.

315
00:24:35,411 --> 00:24:38,581
Clearly. Has it become practice
to hold a full criminal trial...

316
00:24:38,748 --> 00:24:41,626
...to deal with a simple matter
of underage magic?

317
00:24:50,009 --> 00:24:53,596
Those in favor of conviction?

318
00:25:02,397 --> 00:25:07,360
Those in favor
of clearing the accused of all charges?

319
00:25:21,457 --> 00:25:23,751
Cleared of all charges.

320
00:25:24,460 --> 00:25:26,295
[CROWD CHATTERING]

321
00:25:26,754 --> 00:25:28,506
Professor.

322
00:25:38,558 --> 00:25:39,767
[DOG BARKING]

323
00:25:41,436 --> 00:25:44,522
[WHISPERING]
Padfoot. Are you barking mad?

324
00:25:44,689 --> 00:25:47,066
You'll blow the entire operation.

325
00:25:55,450 --> 00:25:58,077
Sirius, what are you doing here?
If somebody sees you...

326
00:25:58,286 --> 00:26:00,872
SIRIUS:
I had to see you off, didn't I?

327
00:26:02,665 --> 00:26:05,168
What's life without a little risk?

328
00:26:05,376 --> 00:26:07,712
I don't wanna see you
get chucked back in Azkaban.

329
00:26:07,879 --> 00:26:09,338
Oh, don't worry about me.

330
00:26:09,797 --> 00:26:14,802
Anyway, I wanted you to have this.

331
00:26:20,141 --> 00:26:23,186
Original Order of the Phoenix.

332
00:26:23,728 --> 00:26:25,438
Marlene McKinnon.

333
00:26:25,605 --> 00:26:28,191
She was killed
two weeks after this was taken.

334
00:26:28,566 --> 00:26:31,736
Voldemort wiped out her entire family.

335
00:26:32,153 --> 00:26:33,946
Frank and Alice Longbottom.

336
00:26:34,113 --> 00:26:35,615
HARRY:
Neville's parents.

337
00:26:35,823 --> 00:26:39,452
They suffered a fate worse than death,
you ask me.

338
00:26:41,412 --> 00:26:43,873
It's been 14 years.

339
00:26:44,707 --> 00:26:48,920
And still a day doesn't go by
I don't miss your dad.

340
00:26:53,591 --> 00:26:56,260
Do you really think
there's going to be a war, Sirius?

341
00:26:58,930 --> 00:27:01,974
It feels like it did before.

342
00:27:06,187 --> 00:27:07,980
You keep it.

343
00:27:08,481 --> 00:27:12,860
Anyway, I suppose
you're the young ones now.

344
00:27:15,071 --> 00:27:16,906
I'll see you at the train.

345
00:27:17,073 --> 00:27:19,116
WOMAN 1:
Bye-bye, darling.

346
00:27:19,992 --> 00:27:21,494
I love you.

347
00:27:22,245 --> 00:27:24,247
WOMAN 2:
Hold my hand, lovey.

348
00:27:24,497 --> 00:27:26,791
MAN: There they are.
They're in the far carriage.

349
00:27:26,958 --> 00:27:28,251
Bye.

350
00:27:30,962 --> 00:27:32,630
[VOICES WHISPERING]

351
00:28:10,459 --> 00:28:13,379
I'm surprised the Ministry's
still letting you walk around free.

352
00:28:13,546 --> 00:28:15,047
Better enjoy it while you can.

353
00:28:15,214 --> 00:28:18,509
I expect there's a cell in Azkaban
with your name on it.

354
00:28:21,095 --> 00:28:25,057
-What'd I tell you? Complete nutter.
-Just stay away from me!

355
00:28:26,267 --> 00:28:28,102
It's only Malfoy.

356
00:28:28,936 --> 00:28:30,771
What'd you expect?

357
00:28:50,750 --> 00:28:51,918
Hi, guys.

358
00:28:52,084 --> 00:28:53,753
-Hey, Neville.
-Hey there, Neville.

359
00:29:06,807 --> 00:29:08,351
What is it?

360
00:29:10,519 --> 00:29:13,773
RON: What's what?
HARRY: That. Pulling the carriage.

361
00:29:14,607 --> 00:29:16,984
Nothing's pulling the carriage, Harry.

362
00:29:17,568 --> 00:29:19,779
It's pulling itself, like always.

363
00:29:33,417 --> 00:29:35,628
GIRL:
You're not going mad.

364
00:29:38,214 --> 00:29:40,508
I can see them too.

365
00:29:41,717 --> 00:29:44,303
You're just as sane as I am.

366
00:29:49,141 --> 00:29:51,185
Everyone, this is Loony Love--

367
00:29:54,021 --> 00:29:55,898
Luna Lovegood.

368
00:29:59,819 --> 00:30:02,154
What an interesting necklace.

369
00:30:02,697 --> 00:30:04,865
It's a charm, actually.

370
00:30:06,242 --> 00:30:07,827
Keeps away the Nargles.

371
00:30:11,622 --> 00:30:13,124
Hungry.

372
00:30:13,791 --> 00:30:15,751
I hope there's pudding.

373
00:30:16,752 --> 00:30:18,587
RON [WHISPERING]:
What's a Nargle?

374
00:30:18,754 --> 00:30:20,339
HERMIONE [WHISPERING]:
No idea.

375
00:30:21,048 --> 00:30:23,050
[STUDENTS CHATTERING]

376
00:30:33,060 --> 00:30:34,687
DUMBLEDORE:
Good evening, children.

377
00:30:35,980 --> 00:30:38,691
Now, we have two changes
in staffing this year.

378
00:30:38,858 --> 00:30:41,902
We're pleased to welcome back
Professor Grubbly-Plank...

379
00:30:42,069 --> 00:30:44,655
...who'll be taking
Care of Magical Creatures...

380
00:30:44,822 --> 00:30:48,284
...while Professor Hagrid
is on temporary leave.

381
00:30:49,118 --> 00:30:53,122
We also wish to welcome our new
Defense Against the Dark Arts teacher...

382
00:30:53,289 --> 00:30:55,374
...Professor Dolores Umbridge.

383
00:30:55,583 --> 00:30:56,625
[UMBRIDGE GIGGLES]

384
00:30:56,792 --> 00:31:00,504
And I'm sure you'll all join me
in wishing the professor good luck.

385
00:31:01,297 --> 00:31:04,717
Now, as usual, our caretaker, Mr. Filch,
has asked me to remind you--

386
00:31:04,884 --> 00:31:06,302
[UMBRIDGE CLEARS THROAT]

387
00:31:17,396 --> 00:31:18,731
[WHISPERING]
She was at my hearing.

388
00:31:18,898 --> 00:31:20,107
She works for Fudge.

389
00:31:20,274 --> 00:31:25,988
UMBRIDGE: Thank you, headmaster,
for those kind words of welcome.

390
00:31:27,364 --> 00:31:31,035
And how lovely to see all your bright...

391
00:31:31,202 --> 00:31:34,038
...happy faces smiling up at me.

392
00:31:34,413 --> 00:31:39,585
I'm sure we're all going
to be very good friends.

393
00:31:39,752 --> 00:31:42,004
-That's likely.
-That's likely.

394
00:31:44,840 --> 00:31:47,802
The Ministry of Magic
has always considered...

395
00:31:47,968 --> 00:31:53,641
...the education of young witches
and wizards to be of vital importance.

396
00:31:53,933 --> 00:31:56,227
Although each headmaster...

397
00:31:56,393 --> 00:32:01,232
...has brought something new
to this historic school...

398
00:32:02,775 --> 00:32:08,948
...progress for the sake of progress
must be discouraged.

399
00:32:09,657 --> 00:32:13,494
Let us preserve
what must be preserved...

400
00:32:13,661 --> 00:32:17,164
...perfect what can be perfected...

401
00:32:17,331 --> 00:32:21,544
...and prune practices
that ought to be...

402
00:32:21,710 --> 00:32:23,504
[WHISPERS]
...prohibited.

403
00:32:23,671 --> 00:32:25,297
[GIGGLES]

404
00:32:31,011 --> 00:32:32,805
DUMBLEDORE:
Thank you, Professor Umbridge.

405
00:32:32,972 --> 00:32:35,141
That really was most illuminating.

406
00:32:35,307 --> 00:32:39,687
RON: illuminating? What a load of waffle.
-What's it mean?

407
00:32:40,396 --> 00:32:42,565
DUMBLEDORE:
Magic is forbidden in the corridors...

408
00:32:42,731 --> 00:32:46,318
It means the Ministry's
interfering at Hogwarts.

409
00:33:06,088 --> 00:33:07,840
HARRY:
Dean, Seamus.

410
00:33:08,132 --> 00:33:10,259
-Good holiday?
DEAN: All right.

411
00:33:10,634 --> 00:33:12,845
Better than Seamus', anyway.

412
00:33:14,221 --> 00:33:16,515
SEAMUS: Me mum didn't want me
to come back this year.

413
00:33:16,724 --> 00:33:19,977
-Why not?
-Let me see. Uh, because of you.

414
00:33:20,394 --> 00:33:23,772
The Daily Prophet's been saying a lot
of things about you and Dumbledore.

415
00:33:23,939 --> 00:33:25,274
What, your mum believes them?

416
00:33:25,441 --> 00:33:27,359
Nobody was there the night Cedric died.

417
00:33:27,526 --> 00:33:30,613
I guess you should read the Prophet,
then, like your stupid mother.

418
00:33:30,779 --> 00:33:34,283
-Don't talk about my mother.
-I'll go at anyone that calls me a liar.

419
00:33:34,450 --> 00:33:36,952
RON: What's going on?
-He's mad, is what's going on.

420
00:33:37,119 --> 00:33:40,206
Do you believe the rubbish he's come out
with about You-Know-Who?

421
00:33:40,372 --> 00:33:42,041
Yeah. I do.

422
00:33:43,042 --> 00:33:45,002
Has anyone else
got a problem with Harry?

423
00:33:54,428 --> 00:33:56,847
-You all right?
-Fine.

424
00:33:57,014 --> 00:33:59,808
Seamus was bang out of order, mate.

425
00:34:00,392 --> 00:34:04,146
-But he'll come through, you'll see.
- I said, I'm fine, Ron.

426
00:34:07,816 --> 00:34:12,279
Right. I'll just leave you
to your thoughts, then.

427
00:34:23,540 --> 00:34:25,542
[VOICES WHISPERING]

428
00:34:38,722 --> 00:34:40,474
[HARRY PANTING]

429
00:34:40,641 --> 00:34:41,684
VOLDEMORT:
Harry.

430
00:34:47,398 --> 00:34:48,857
[HARRY GASPS]

431
00:34:54,488 --> 00:34:56,949
[STUDENTS CHATTERING
AND LAUGHING]

432
00:34:57,116 --> 00:34:59,326
GIRL:
Bring it over here. Over here.

433
00:35:00,202 --> 00:35:02,288
BOY:
Oh, go on, Seamus. Go on, get it.

434
00:35:02,454 --> 00:35:03,956
[SEAMUS GRUNTS]

435
00:35:10,337 --> 00:35:12,381
[STUDENTS LAUGHING]

436
00:35:18,721 --> 00:35:20,139
Good morning, children.

437
00:35:22,141 --> 00:35:27,313
Ordinary Wizarding Level examinations.

438
00:35:27,479 --> 00:35:30,065
O-W-Ls.

439
00:35:30,232 --> 00:35:34,820
More commonly known as OWLs.

440
00:35:34,987 --> 00:35:38,115
Study hard and you will be rewarded.

441
00:35:38,449 --> 00:35:43,704
Fail to do so,
and the consequences may be severe.

442
00:35:49,293 --> 00:35:54,340
Your previous instruction in this subject
has been disturbingly uneven.

443
00:35:54,506 --> 00:35:56,675
But you'll be pleased to know,
from now on...

444
00:35:56,884 --> 00:36:00,346
...you will be following a carefully
structured, Ministry-approved...

445
00:36:00,512 --> 00:36:03,182
...course of defensive magic. Yes?

446
00:36:04,516 --> 00:36:07,144
There's nothing in here
about using defensive spells?

447
00:36:07,311 --> 00:36:08,854
Using spells? Ha-ha!

448
00:36:09,021 --> 00:36:12,483
Well, I can't imagine why you would
need to use spells in my classroom.

449
00:36:14,193 --> 00:36:15,778
We're not gonna use magic?

450
00:36:15,944 --> 00:36:20,949
You'll be learning about defensive spells
in a secure, risk-free way.

451
00:36:21,116 --> 00:36:23,869
What use is that?
If we're attacked, it won't be risk-free.

452
00:36:24,036 --> 00:36:26,997
UMBRIDGE: Students will raise their
hands when they speak in my class.

453
00:36:30,626 --> 00:36:33,045
It is the view of the Ministry...

454
00:36:33,212 --> 00:36:35,964
...that a theoretical knowledge
will be sufficient...

455
00:36:36,131 --> 00:36:38,092
...10 get you through your examinations...

456
00:36:38,258 --> 00:36:40,719
...which, after all,
is what school is all about.

457
00:36:40,928 --> 00:36:43,680
And how's theory supposed to prepare us
for what's out there?

458
00:36:43,847 --> 00:36:45,891
There is nothing out there, dear.

459
00:36:46,058 --> 00:36:49,061
Who do you imagine
wants to attack children like yourself?

460
00:36:49,228 --> 00:36:52,523
Oh, I don't know. Maybe Lord Voldemort.

461
00:36:52,689 --> 00:36:54,358
[STUDENTS WHISPERING]

462
00:37:03,200 --> 00:37:07,704
Now, let me make this quite plain.

463
00:37:08,247 --> 00:37:09,706
You have been told...

464
00:37:09,873 --> 00:37:15,254
...that a certain dark wizard
is at large once again.

465
00:37:15,462 --> 00:37:20,551
-This is a lie.
-It's not a lie. I saw him. I fought him.

466
00:37:20,717 --> 00:37:22,344
UMBRIDGE:
Detention, Mr. Potter.

467
00:37:22,511 --> 00:37:24,680
Cedric Diggory dropped dead
of his own accord?

468
00:37:24,847 --> 00:37:27,266
Cedric Diggory's death
was a tragic accident.

469
00:37:27,474 --> 00:37:29,601
It was murder. Voldemort killed him.

470
00:37:29,768 --> 00:37:31,270
Enough!

471
00:37:31,979 --> 00:37:33,605
Enough.

472
00:37:33,772 --> 00:37:37,401
See me later, Mr. Potter. My office.

473
00:37:37,568 --> 00:37:39,111
[GIGGLES]

474
00:37:51,206 --> 00:37:53,208
[CATS MEWLING]

475
00:37:54,168 --> 00:37:55,794
[KNOCKS]

476
00:38:02,843 --> 00:38:04,052
UMBRIDGE:
Come in.

477
00:38:09,308 --> 00:38:11,226
Good evening, Mr. Potter.

478
00:38:11,852 --> 00:38:13,145
Sit.

479
00:38:18,525 --> 00:38:20,652
[CATS PURRING]

480
00:38:20,819 --> 00:38:24,740
You're going to be doing some lines
for me today, Mr. Potter.

481
00:38:24,907 --> 00:38:26,783
No, not with your quill.

482
00:38:27,034 --> 00:38:30,204
Going to be using
a rather special one of mine.

483
00:38:35,334 --> 00:38:36,752
Now...

484
00:38:37,711 --> 00:38:43,592
...I want you to write,
"I must not tell lies."

485
00:38:45,677 --> 00:38:47,554
How many times?

486
00:38:48,055 --> 00:38:52,684
Well, let's say for as long as it takes
for the message to sink in.

487
00:38:54,686 --> 00:38:56,355
You haven't given me any ink.

488
00:38:56,563 --> 00:38:58,065
Oh, you won't need any ink.

489
00:39:16,583 --> 00:39:18,210
[HARRY GRUNTING]

490
00:39:49,241 --> 00:39:50,742
Yes?

491
00:39:58,125 --> 00:40:01,461
-Nothing.
-That's right.

492
00:40:02,379 --> 00:40:06,341
Because you know, deep down...

493
00:40:06,508 --> 00:40:08,635
...you deserve to be punished.

494
00:40:09,761 --> 00:40:11,930
Don't you, Mr. Potter?

495
00:40:16,143 --> 00:40:17,769
Go on.

496
00:40:26,778 --> 00:40:29,072
FRED: Skiving Snackboxes.
-Sweets that make you ill.

497
00:40:29,239 --> 00:40:30,866
Get out of class whenever you like.

498
00:40:31,033 --> 00:40:34,786
Obtain hours of pleasure
from unprofitable boredom.

499
00:40:35,787 --> 00:40:37,122
Care for another?

500
00:40:37,289 --> 00:40:39,207
RON: I'm not asking you
to write all of it for me.

501
00:40:39,374 --> 00:40:40,417
HERMIONE:
Oh, please.

502
00:40:40,584 --> 00:40:42,961
RON: I've been busy studying
for these stupid OWL exams.

503
00:40:43,462 --> 00:40:45,255
I'll do the introduction. That's all.

504
00:40:45,422 --> 00:40:49,176
Hermione, you're honestly
the most wonderful person I've ever met.

505
00:40:49,343 --> 00:40:53,597
-And if I'm ever rude to you again...
-I'll know you've gone back to normal.

506
00:40:58,685 --> 00:41:00,729
What's wrong with your hand?

507
00:41:01,271 --> 00:41:02,731
Nothing.

508
00:41:03,982 --> 00:41:05,901
The other hand.

509
00:41:08,403 --> 00:41:10,238
-You've got to tell Dumbledore.
-No.

510
00:41:10,405 --> 00:41:12,616
Dumbledore's got enough
on his mind right now.

511
00:41:12,783 --> 00:41:14,910
I don't want to give
Umbridge the satisfaction.

512
00:41:15,077 --> 00:41:17,496
Bloody hell, Harry.
The woman's torturing you.

513
00:41:17,704 --> 00:41:21,625
-If the parents knew about this...
-I haven't got any of those, have I, Ron?

514
00:41:24,419 --> 00:41:26,880
Harry, you've got to report this.

515
00:41:27,047 --> 00:41:30,592
-It's perfectly simple. You're being--
-No, it's not.

516
00:41:30,759 --> 00:41:33,595
Hermione, whatever this is,
it's not simple.

517
00:41:34,638 --> 00:41:36,723
You don't understand.

518
00:41:39,267 --> 00:41:41,228
Then help us to.

519
00:41:48,985 --> 00:41:50,862
[SCREECHING]

520
00:41:55,909 --> 00:41:57,786
HARRY:
Dear Padfoot...

521
00:41:58,328 --> 00:42:00,038
...I hope you're all right.

522
00:42:00,247 --> 00:42:04,835
It's starting to get colder here.
Winter is definitely on the way.

523
00:42:07,462 --> 00:42:12,259
In spite of being back at Hogwarts,
I feel more alone than ever.

524
00:42:12,426 --> 00:42:13,552
[WAILING IN THE DISTANCE]

525
00:42:13,760 --> 00:42:16,388
I know you, of all people,
will understand.

526
00:42:50,464 --> 00:42:52,674
Hello, Harry Potter.

527
00:42:55,302 --> 00:42:59,931
-Your feet. Aren't they cold?
-Bit.

528
00:43:00,849 --> 00:43:04,895
Unfortunately, all my shoes
have mysteriously disappeared.

529
00:43:05,437 --> 00:43:08,523
I suspect Nargles are behind it.

530
00:43:14,863 --> 00:43:17,616
HARRY: What are they?
LUNA: They're called Thestrals.

531
00:43:17,824 --> 00:43:19,034
[THESTRAL WAILING]

532
00:43:19,201 --> 00:43:24,247
They're quite gentle, really, but people
avoid them because they're a bit...

533
00:43:27,167 --> 00:43:28,835
Different.

534
00:43:31,922 --> 00:43:34,299
But why can't the others see them?

535
00:43:34,466 --> 00:43:37,969
They can only be seen
by people who've seen death.

536
00:43:40,096 --> 00:43:42,724
So you've known someone
who's died, then?

537
00:43:42,891 --> 00:43:44,518
My mum.

538
00:43:45,060 --> 00:43:49,981
She was quite an extraordinary witch,
but she did like to experiment...

539
00:43:50,148 --> 00:43:53,443
...and one day,
one of her spells went badly wrong.

540
00:43:53,610 --> 00:43:55,987
-I was 9.
-I'm sorry.

541
00:43:56,571 --> 00:43:58,782
Yes, it was rather horrible.

542
00:43:58,949 --> 00:44:04,287
I do feel very sad about it sometimes,
but I've got Dad.

543
00:44:06,498 --> 00:44:08,500
We both believe you, by the way.

544
00:44:08,667 --> 00:44:10,210
[THESTRAL WAILS]

545
00:44:12,212 --> 00:44:15,215
That He-Who-Must-Not-Be-Named
is back, and you fought him...

546
00:44:15,382 --> 00:44:18,510
...and the Ministry and the Prophet
are conspiring against you.

547
00:44:18,677 --> 00:44:23,014
Thanks. It seems you're about
the only ones that do.

548
00:44:23,181 --> 00:44:24,516
I don't think that's true.

549
00:44:26,893 --> 00:44:30,021
But I suppose
that's how he wants you to feel.

550
00:44:30,188 --> 00:44:31,982
What do you mean?

551
00:44:32,607 --> 00:44:34,484
Well, if I were You-Know-Who...

552
00:44:34,943 --> 00:44:38,530
...I'd want you to feel cut off
from everyone else...

553
00:44:38,697 --> 00:44:41,408
...because if it's just you alone...

554
00:44:42,242 --> 00:44:44,578
...you're not as much of a threat.

555
00:45:02,220 --> 00:45:06,975
-Do you ever stop eating?
-What? I'm hungry.

556
00:45:10,353 --> 00:45:11,438
Harry.

557
00:45:13,231 --> 00:45:14,482
Can I join you?

558
00:45:16,443 --> 00:45:19,529
UMBRIDGE: Pardon me, professor,
but what exactly are you insinuating?

559
00:45:19,696 --> 00:45:22,490
McGonagall: I am merely requesting
that when it comes to my students...

560
00:45:22,657 --> 00:45:26,912
...you conform to the prescribed
disciplinary practices.

561
00:45:27,078 --> 00:45:28,747
UMBRIDGE:
So silly of me, but it sounds...

562
00:45:28,955 --> 00:45:33,043
...as if you're questioning my authority
in my own classroom...

563
00:45:33,209 --> 00:45:34,544
...Minerva.

564
00:45:34,711 --> 00:45:39,174
Not at all, Dolores,
merely your medieval methods.

565
00:45:39,466 --> 00:45:41,927
I am sorry, dear.

566
00:45:42,093 --> 00:45:45,430
But to question my practices
is to question the Ministry...

567
00:45:45,597 --> 00:45:48,725
...and by extension, the minister himself.

568
00:45:48,892 --> 00:45:50,477
I am a tolerant woman...

569
00:45:50,644 --> 00:45:55,732
...but the one thing
I will not stand for is disloyalty.

570
00:45:57,484 --> 00:45:59,277
Disloyalty.

571
00:46:00,987 --> 00:46:04,950
Things at Hogwarts
are far worse than I feared.

572
00:46:05,116 --> 00:46:08,620
Cornelius will want
to take immediate action.

573
00:46:20,006 --> 00:46:21,925
REPORTER:
What's happened to Dumbledore?

574
00:46:22,092 --> 00:46:24,636
FUDGE:
Having already revolutionized...

575
00:46:24,803 --> 00:46:27,722
...the teaching
of Defense Against the Dark Arts...

576
00:46:28,139 --> 00:46:33,520
...Dolores Umbridge will,
as high inquisitor, have powers...

577
00:46:34,312 --> 00:46:39,317
...to address the seriously falling
standards at Hogwarts School.

578
00:46:45,824 --> 00:46:46,908
[GIRL WHIMPERS]

579
00:46:47,075 --> 00:46:49,244
Just one question, dear.

580
00:46:49,411 --> 00:46:53,623
You've been in this post
how long, exactly?

581
00:46:55,959 --> 00:46:58,253
[BOYS GRUNT AND COUGH]

582
00:46:58,753 --> 00:47:00,255
[BOYS YELP]

583
00:47:00,422 --> 00:47:05,510
You applied first for the Defense Against
the Dark Arts post, is that correct?

584
00:47:05,677 --> 00:47:07,679
Yes.

585
00:47:08,096 --> 00:47:10,724
But you were unsuccessful?

586
00:47:11,933 --> 00:47:13,351
Obviously.

587
00:47:13,560 --> 00:47:14,561
[RON CHUCKLES]

588
00:47:21,860 --> 00:47:23,862
[STUDENTS CHEERING]

589
00:47:41,588 --> 00:47:43,214
[STUDENTS GASP]

590
00:47:46,718 --> 00:47:50,138
Could you please predict something
for me?

591
00:47:51,890 --> 00:47:53,099
I'm sorry?

592
00:47:53,391 --> 00:47:55,810
[STUDENTS SINGING]

593
00:47:58,313 --> 00:48:00,523
Move those mouths.

594
00:48:06,654 --> 00:48:09,741
One teensy little prophecy?

595
00:48:15,622 --> 00:48:17,123
Pity.

596
00:48:17,624 --> 00:48:20,043
No, wait. Wait, no.
I think I do see something.

597
00:48:20,210 --> 00:48:22,420
Yes, I do. Something dark.

598
00:48:22,670 --> 00:48:27,217
You are in grave danger.

599
00:48:28,676 --> 00:48:30,428
Lovely.

600
00:48:40,647 --> 00:48:42,774
Cho. What's going on?

601
00:48:42,941 --> 00:48:45,276
It's Professor Trelawney.

602
00:48:52,450 --> 00:48:54,869
[TRELAWNEY STAMMERING]

603
00:49:07,757 --> 00:49:09,175
TRELAWNEY:
Ooh!

604
00:49:15,098 --> 00:49:18,601
[SOBBING]
Sixteen years I've lived and taught here.

605
00:49:18,768 --> 00:49:21,688
Hogwarts is my home.

606
00:49:23,606 --> 00:49:25,483
You can't do this.

607
00:49:26,943 --> 00:49:29,195
Actually, I can.

608
00:49:35,201 --> 00:49:36,995
[TRELAWNEY SOBBING]

609
00:49:38,079 --> 00:49:39,455
Something you'd like to say?

610
00:49:39,622 --> 00:49:42,292
Oh, there are several things
I would like to say.

611
00:49:42,834 --> 00:49:44,210
There... Shh. Shh.

612
00:49:44,377 --> 00:49:45,837
[DOOR OPENS]

613
00:49:58,349 --> 00:50:03,021
Professor McGonagall, might I ask you
to escort Sybil back inside?

614
00:50:04,314 --> 00:50:06,774
Sybil, dear. This way.

615
00:50:06,941 --> 00:50:08,443
Thank you.

616
00:50:09,611 --> 00:50:13,656
UMBRIDGE: Dumbledore, may I remind
you that under the terms...

617
00:50:13,823 --> 00:50:17,076
...of Educational Decree Number 23,
as enacted by the minister--

618
00:50:17,243 --> 00:50:20,413
You have the right
to dismiss my teachers.

619
00:50:20,580 --> 00:50:24,167
You do not, however, have the authority
to banish them from the grounds.

620
00:50:24,334 --> 00:50:27,378
That power remains with the headmaster.

621
00:50:29,380 --> 00:50:30,632
For now.

622
00:50:37,055 --> 00:50:39,057
DUMBLEDORE:
Don't you all have studying to do?

623
00:50:39,265 --> 00:50:40,391
Professor.

624
00:50:42,268 --> 00:50:43,353
Professor?

625
00:50:43,811 --> 00:50:46,606
Professor Dumbledore. Professor!

626
00:50:46,773 --> 00:50:48,900
Professor Dumbledore.

627
00:50:59,577 --> 00:51:01,704
HERMIONE:
That foul, evil, old gargoyle.

628
00:51:02,288 --> 00:51:04,457
We're not learning how
to defend ourselves.

629
00:51:04,624 --> 00:51:07,293
We're not learning how
to pass our OWLs.

630
00:51:07,627 --> 00:51:09,671
She's taking over the entire school.

631
00:51:09,837 --> 00:51:14,509
FUDGE [ON RADIO]: Security has been
and will remain the Ministry's top priority.

632
00:51:14,676 --> 00:51:17,512
Furthermore,
we have convincing evidence...

633
00:51:17,679 --> 00:51:20,556
...that these disappearances
are the work...

634
00:51:20,723 --> 00:51:24,102
...of notorious
mass murderer Sirius Black.

635
00:51:24,852 --> 00:51:26,437
SIRIUS:
Harry.

636
00:51:26,646 --> 00:51:28,356
Sirius.

637
00:51:29,107 --> 00:51:31,776
-What are you doing here?
SIRIUS: Answering your letter.

638
00:51:31,943 --> 00:51:34,862
You said you were worried
about Umbridge. What's she doing?

639
00:51:35,029 --> 00:51:36,948
Training you to kill half-breeds?

640
00:51:37,115 --> 00:51:40,118
-She's not letting us use magic at all.
SIRIUS: Well, I'm not surprised.

641
00:51:40,451 --> 00:51:44,497
The latest intelligence is that Fudge
doesn't want you trained in combat.

642
00:51:44,664 --> 00:51:45,707
RON:
Combat?

643
00:51:46,207 --> 00:51:49,127
What does he think,
we're forming some sort of wizard army?

644
00:51:49,335 --> 00:51:50,670
That's exactly what he thinks.

645
00:51:50,837 --> 00:51:54,841
That Dumbledore is assembling
his own forces to take on the Ministry.

646
00:51:55,341 --> 00:51:58,636
He's becoming more paranoid
by the minute.

647
00:51:58,970 --> 00:52:02,473
The others wouldn't want me
telling you this, Harry...

648
00:52:02,974 --> 00:52:05,810
...but things aren't going at all well
with the Order.

649
00:52:05,977 --> 00:52:08,646
Fudge is blocking the truth
at every turn...

650
00:52:08,855 --> 00:52:12,859
...and these disappearances
are just how it started before.

651
00:52:13,609 --> 00:52:16,946
Voldemort is on the move.

652
00:52:17,238 --> 00:52:18,281
Well, what can we do?

653
00:52:18,448 --> 00:52:19,490
[DOOR OPENS]

654
00:52:19,657 --> 00:52:20,867
[WHISPERING]
Someone's coming.

655
00:52:21,034 --> 00:52:23,161
I'm sorry I can't be of more help.

656
00:52:23,369 --> 00:52:28,374
But for now, at least,
it looks like you're on your own.

657
00:52:37,717 --> 00:52:39,677
[THUNDER CRASHES]

658
00:52:39,886 --> 00:52:42,180
He really is out there, isn't he?

659
00:52:44,015 --> 00:52:46,684
We've got to be able
to defend ourselves.

660
00:52:47,268 --> 00:52:51,022
And if Umbridge refuses to teach us how,
we need someone who will.

661
00:52:52,315 --> 00:52:54,317
[THUNDER CRASHING]

662
00:53:08,039 --> 00:53:10,208
VOLDEMORT:
Harry.

663
00:53:19,801 --> 00:53:22,178
HARRY: This is mad.
Who'd wanna be taught by me?

664
00:53:22,345 --> 00:53:23,554
I'm a nutter, remember?

665
00:53:23,721 --> 00:53:28,226
Look on the bright side: you can't
be any worse than old toad face.

666
00:53:28,476 --> 00:53:31,938
-Thanks, Ron.
-I'm here for you, mate.

667
00:53:32,438 --> 00:53:34,774
HARRY:
Who's supposed to be meeting us, then?

668
00:53:34,941 --> 00:53:37,068
HERMIONE:
Just a couple of people.

669
00:53:42,073 --> 00:53:43,408
Lovely spot.

670
00:53:43,574 --> 00:53:45,451
[GOAT BLEATING]

671
00:53:47,245 --> 00:53:49,372
Thought it would be safer
off the beaten track.

672
00:53:49,539 --> 00:53:51,707
MAN:
Matey, come back here.

673
00:53:57,755 --> 00:53:59,257
Um...

674
00:54:00,133 --> 00:54:01,300
Hi.

675
00:54:01,717 --> 00:54:04,595
So you all know why we're here.

676
00:54:04,762 --> 00:54:06,013
We need a teacher.

677
00:54:07,723 --> 00:54:09,892
A proper teacher.

678
00:54:10,184 --> 00:54:13,354
One who's had experience defending
themselves against the Dark Arts.

679
00:54:13,521 --> 00:54:15,273
-Why?
RON: Why?

680
00:54:15,481 --> 00:54:17,525
Because You-Know-Who's back,
you toss pot.

681
00:54:17,692 --> 00:54:19,318
-So he says.
HERMIONE: So Dumbledore says.

682
00:54:19,485 --> 00:54:21,571
BOY:
So Dumbledore says because he says.

683
00:54:21,737 --> 00:54:24,115
The point is, where's the proof?

684
00:54:25,491 --> 00:54:28,536
If Potter could tell us more
about how Diggory got killed...

685
00:54:31,622 --> 00:54:35,293
I'm not gonna talk about Cedric, so if
that's why you're here, clear out now.

686
00:54:35,501 --> 00:54:36,627
[WHISPERS]
Come on, Hermione.

687
00:54:36,794 --> 00:54:39,005
They're here because they think
I'm some sort of freak.

688
00:54:39,172 --> 00:54:41,799
Is it true you can produce
a Patronus Charm?

689
00:54:45,136 --> 00:54:46,554
HERMIONE:
Yes.

690
00:54:48,014 --> 00:54:49,474
I've seen it.

691
00:54:49,640 --> 00:54:51,767
Blimey, Harry.
I didn't know you could do that.

692
00:54:52,435 --> 00:54:56,564
And he killed a basilisk, with the sword
in Dumbledore's office.

693
00:54:56,731 --> 00:54:57,982
It's true.

694
00:54:58,149 --> 00:55:00,902
Third year, he fought off
about a hundred Dementors at once.

695
00:55:02,195 --> 00:55:04,989
Last year, he really did fight off
You-Know-Who in the flesh.

696
00:55:05,156 --> 00:55:06,532
Wait.

697
00:55:07,158 --> 00:55:11,704
Look, it all sounds great
when you say it like that...

698
00:55:11,871 --> 00:55:15,458
...but the truth is,
most of that was just luck.

699
00:55:15,708 --> 00:55:19,462
I didn't know what I was doing
half the time. I nearly always had help.

700
00:55:19,629 --> 00:55:23,132
-He's just being modest.
-No, Hermione, I'm not.

701
00:55:25,676 --> 00:55:30,348
Facing this stuff in real life
is not like school.

702
00:55:31,390 --> 00:55:34,852
In school, if you make a mistake,
you can just try again tomorrow.

703
00:55:35,061 --> 00:55:36,562
But out there...

704
00:55:37,104 --> 00:55:40,399
...when you're a second away
from being murdered...

705
00:55:40,566 --> 00:55:44,278
...or watching a friend die
right before your eyes...

706
00:55:47,073 --> 00:55:48,866
You don't know what that's like.

707
00:55:58,626 --> 00:56:00,586
HERMIONE:
You're right, Harry, we don't.

708
00:56:01,295 --> 00:56:03,381
That's why we need your help.

709
00:56:03,589 --> 00:56:06,467
Because if we're going to have
any chance at beating...

710
00:56:08,678 --> 00:56:09,845
...Voldemort...

711
00:56:13,266 --> 00:56:15,017
He's really back?

712
00:56:37,415 --> 00:56:38,791
Right. First we need to find
a place to practice...

713
00:56:38,958 --> 00:56:40,585
...where Umbridge won't find out.

714
00:56:40,751 --> 00:56:42,920
-The Shrieking Shack.
-It's too small.

715
00:56:43,129 --> 00:56:46,048
-Forbidden Forest?
-Not bloody likely.

716
00:56:46,215 --> 00:56:48,301
Harry, what happens
if Umbridge does find out?

717
00:56:48,467 --> 00:56:49,635
HERMIONE:
Who cares?

718
00:56:50,261 --> 00:56:55,099
I mean, it's sort of exciting, isn't it,
breaking the rules?

719
00:56:55,266 --> 00:56:57,560
Who are you and what have you done
with Hermione?

720
00:56:58,269 --> 00:57:01,939
Anyway, at least we know
one positive thing that came from today.

721
00:57:02,148 --> 00:57:03,399
HARRY:
What's that?

722
00:57:05,151 --> 00:57:07,778
Cho couldn't take her eyes off you,
could she?

723
00:57:10,531 --> 00:57:13,618
HARRY: Right. Over the next few days,
we should each come up...

724
00:57:13,784 --> 00:57:16,621
...with a couple of possibilities
of places we can practice.

725
00:57:16,787 --> 00:57:20,625
We've got to make sure, wherever it is,
there's no chance she can find us.

726
00:57:20,791 --> 00:57:22,668
NEVILLE:
Will do, Harry.

727
00:57:25,171 --> 00:57:27,673
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

728
00:57:31,344 --> 00:57:35,473
UMBRIDGE: All student organizations
are henceforth disbanded.

729
00:57:35,681 --> 00:57:38,267
Any student in noncompliance
will be expelled.

730
00:57:38,434 --> 00:57:39,477
[NEVILLE GRUNTS]

731
00:57:39,685 --> 00:57:41,437
Watch where you're going, Longbottom.

732
00:57:41,604 --> 00:57:43,189
[GOYLE LAUGHS]

733
00:57:51,030 --> 00:57:53,366
[DUST TRICKLING]

734
00:58:17,640 --> 00:58:21,894
HERMIONE: You've done it, Neville.
You found the Room of Requirement.

735
00:58:22,061 --> 00:58:23,187
RON:
The what?

736
00:58:23,354 --> 00:58:25,773
HERMIONE: It's also known as
the Come and Go Room.

737
00:58:25,940 --> 00:58:29,360
The Room of Requirement only appears
when a person has real need of it.

738
00:58:29,527 --> 00:58:32,196
And it's always equipped
for the seeker's needs.

739
00:58:32,363 --> 00:58:36,117
RON:
So say you really needed the toilet...

740
00:58:37,284 --> 00:58:42,123
Charming, Ronald.
But, yes, that is the general idea.

741
00:58:42,289 --> 00:58:47,169
It's brilliant. It's like Hogwarts
wants us to fight back.

742
00:58:58,264 --> 00:58:59,765
Expelliarmus.

743
00:59:00,266 --> 00:59:01,559
NIGEL:
Whoa!

744
00:59:04,854 --> 00:59:06,230
NEVILLE:
I'm hopeless.

745
00:59:06,397 --> 00:59:10,192
You're just flourishing your wand
too much. Try it like this. Expelliarmus.

746
00:59:13,571 --> 00:59:17,575
UMBRIDGE: You will please copy
the approved text four times...

747
00:59:17,783 --> 00:59:20,786
...to ensure maximum retention.

748
00:59:21,120 --> 00:59:24,832
-There will be no need to talk.
-No need to think's more like it.

749
00:59:24,999 --> 00:59:27,835
NEVILLE [WHISPERS]: Expelliarmus.
UMBRIDGE: Wands away.

750
00:59:39,972 --> 00:59:43,058
Stunning is one of the most useful spells
in your arsenal.

751
00:59:43,225 --> 00:59:45,436
It's a wizard's bread and butter, really.

752
00:59:45,603 --> 00:59:49,190
So, um, come on, then, Nigel.
Give it your best shot.

753
00:59:55,696 --> 00:59:57,114
Stupefy!

754
00:59:57,323 --> 00:59:59,450
[NIGEL GASPS]
[HARRY GRUNTS]

755
01:00:01,994 --> 01:00:06,457
HARRY:
Good. Not bad at all, Nigel. Well done.

756
01:00:11,837 --> 01:00:13,923
Don't worry. I'll go easy on you.

757
01:00:14,340 --> 01:00:16,342
Thanks, Ronald.

758
01:00:18,969 --> 01:00:21,138
FRED: Come on, Ron.
GEORGE: Come on, Ron.

759
01:00:21,347 --> 01:00:24,183
BOY 1: You can do it.
BOY 2: Come on, Ron.

760
01:00:24,725 --> 01:00:26,769
-One Sickle.
-You're on.

761
01:00:33,859 --> 01:00:34,860
Stupefy.

762
01:00:35,027 --> 01:00:36,487
[RON YELPS]

763
01:00:38,864 --> 01:00:40,491
[GIRLS LAUGHING]

764
01:00:40,866 --> 01:00:42,868
-Thank you.
-Shut up.

765
01:00:43,202 --> 01:00:47,873
I let her do that.
It's good manners, isn't it?

766
01:00:50,042 --> 01:00:52,586
It was completely intentional.

767
01:00:52,795 --> 01:00:55,172
[SNORES THEN GRUNTS]

768
01:01:18,195 --> 01:01:21,156
UMBRIDGE: Up you come.
Would you like a cup of tea?

769
01:01:23,450 --> 01:01:27,413
Now, focus on a fixed point
and try again.

770
01:01:27,997 --> 01:01:29,164
Expelliarmus.

771
01:01:29,331 --> 01:01:30,833
[WHINING SOUND]

772
01:01:31,542 --> 01:01:34,086
Very good. Keep your concentration.

773
01:01:36,213 --> 01:01:37,715
Great.

774
01:01:38,966 --> 01:01:40,551
A little higher.

775
01:01:46,515 --> 01:01:48,017
Whoa!

776
01:01:49,059 --> 01:01:51,937
I'm okay. I'm okay.

777
01:02:09,955 --> 01:02:12,541
BOY: Stupefy.
GIRL: Stupefy.

778
01:02:14,084 --> 01:02:17,463
UMBRIDGE: Those wishing to join
the Inquisitorial Squad for extra credit...

779
01:02:17,630 --> 01:02:20,507
...may sign up
in the high inquisitor's office.

780
01:02:20,674 --> 01:02:22,301
NIGEL:
Diminuendo.

781
01:02:28,223 --> 01:02:32,519
Working hard is important, but there's
something that matters even more:

782
01:02:32,686 --> 01:02:34,897
Believing in yourself.

783
01:02:35,064 --> 01:02:37,191
GIRL: Expelliarmus.
BOY: Levicorpus. Got it.

784
01:02:37,358 --> 01:02:38,943
Think of it this way.

785
01:02:39,109 --> 01:02:43,113
Every great wizard in history
has started out...

786
01:02:43,489 --> 01:02:47,326
...as nothing more
than what we are now: students.

787
01:02:47,493 --> 01:02:50,496
If they can do it, why not us?

788
01:03:00,589 --> 01:03:02,383
NIGEL: Stupefy.
-Expelliarmus.

789
01:03:04,551 --> 01:03:05,928
CHO:
Expelliarmus.

790
01:03:08,639 --> 01:03:10,140
Expelliarmus.

791
01:03:12,017 --> 01:03:13,727
[ALL GRUNTING]

792
01:03:15,646 --> 01:03:17,022
Reducto.

793
01:03:30,536 --> 01:03:33,497
GIRL 1: Expelliarmus.
-Expelliarmus.

794
01:03:33,664 --> 01:03:36,041
GIRL 2:
Expelliarmus.

795
01:03:39,920 --> 01:03:41,463
Expelliarmus.

796
01:03:41,630 --> 01:03:43,382
[STUDENTS GASP]

797
01:03:45,843 --> 01:03:49,221
Fantastic, Neville. Well done, man.

798
01:03:50,848 --> 01:03:53,017
So that's it for this lesson.

799
01:03:53,183 --> 01:03:55,686
Now, we're not gonna be meeting again
until after the holidays.

800
01:03:55,853 --> 01:03:56,895
[STUDENTS GROAN]

801
01:03:57,062 --> 01:04:00,024
So just keep practicing on your own
as best you can.

802
01:04:00,190 --> 01:04:03,569
And well done, everyone.
Great, great work.

803
01:04:08,365 --> 01:04:09,783
[WHISPERS]
Well done, mate.

804
01:04:09,950 --> 01:04:11,368
Thanks.

805
01:04:17,082 --> 01:04:19,418
GIRL 1:
See you after Christmas.

806
01:04:28,886 --> 01:04:30,929
See you in the Common Room, Harry.

807
01:04:32,347 --> 01:04:35,100
-Thanks a lot, Harry.
-No worries.

808
01:04:35,726 --> 01:04:36,727
HARRY:
Merry Christmas.

809
01:04:36,894 --> 01:04:39,188
GIRL 2: Thank you so much.
HARRY: Not at all. Merry Christmas.

810
01:04:39,646 --> 01:04:42,024
BOY: Thank you, Harry.
-Thank you. Merry Christmas.

811
01:04:42,191 --> 01:04:44,068
-Merry Christmas.
LUNA: Have a good Christmas.

812
01:04:44,234 --> 01:04:46,820
HARRY: Have a great Christmas, Luna.
FRED: We've been thinking.

813
01:04:46,987 --> 01:04:49,406
We could always slip Umbridge
some Puking Pastilles.

814
01:04:49,615 --> 01:04:52,242
Or Fever Fudge. They give you
massive, pus-filled boils--

815
01:04:52,409 --> 01:04:54,912
Sounds great, guys.
Would you excuse me?

816
01:05:05,881 --> 01:05:10,594
Are you all right? I heard Umbridge
gave you a rough time the other day.

817
01:05:10,761 --> 01:05:13,138
Yeah. I'm okay.

818
01:05:13,847 --> 01:05:16,642
Anyway, it's worth it.

819
01:05:21,980 --> 01:05:25,150
It's just, learning all this...

820
01:05:25,943 --> 01:05:29,404
...makes me wonder whether,
if he'd known it...

821
01:05:29,571 --> 01:05:32,282
Cedric did know this stuff.

822
01:05:32,866 --> 01:05:35,285
He was really good.

823
01:05:35,911 --> 01:05:38,664
It's just, Voldemort was better.

824
01:05:43,168 --> 01:05:44,962
You're a really good teacher, Harry.

825
01:05:46,255 --> 01:05:49,174
I've never been able
to stun anything before.

826
01:05:58,308 --> 01:05:59,977
Mistletoe.

827
01:06:03,480 --> 01:06:05,399
Probably full of Nargles, though.

828
01:06:06,483 --> 01:06:08,193
What are Nargles?

829
01:06:08,861 --> 01:06:10,612
No idea.

830
01:06:32,634 --> 01:06:34,845
RON:
Well, how was it?

831
01:06:35,596 --> 01:06:37,347
Wet.

832
01:06:37,764 --> 01:06:39,516
I mean, she was sort of crying.

833
01:06:39,892 --> 01:06:41,852
That bad at it, are you?

834
01:06:42,019 --> 01:06:44,771
I'm sure Harry's kissing
was more than satisfactory.

835
01:06:46,231 --> 01:06:47,441
[RON CHUCKLES]

836
01:06:47,608 --> 01:06:49,776
Cho spends half her time
crying these days.

837
01:06:49,943 --> 01:06:52,237
You'd think a bit of snogging
would cheer her up.

838
01:06:53,739 --> 01:06:56,533
Don't you understand
how she must be feeling?

839
01:07:00,954 --> 01:07:04,416
Well, obviously
she's feeling sad about Cedric...

840
01:07:04,583 --> 01:07:07,669
...and confused about liking Harry
and guilty about kissing him...

841
01:07:07,836 --> 01:07:11,048
...conflicted because Umbridge might
sack her mum from the Ministry...

842
01:07:11,256 --> 01:07:14,968
...and frightened of failing her OWLs
because she's worrying about everything.

843
01:07:16,887 --> 01:07:20,474
One person couldn't feel all that.
They'd explode.

844
01:07:20,641 --> 01:07:23,894
Just because you've got
the emotional range of a teaspoon...

845
01:07:27,314 --> 01:07:28,899
[RON LAUGHS]

846
01:07:29,399 --> 01:07:31,360
[HERMIONE LAUGHING]

847
01:07:40,410 --> 01:07:41,370
VOLDEMORT:
Harry.

848
01:07:42,454 --> 01:07:44,164
[PANTING]

849
01:07:50,128 --> 01:07:53,215
SIRIUS:
Voldemort may be after something.

850
01:07:53,882 --> 01:07:56,885
Something he didn't have last time.

851
01:07:57,719 --> 01:07:58,971
VOLDEMORT:
Harry.

852
01:08:00,597 --> 01:08:01,890
Harry.

853
01:08:02,057 --> 01:08:03,392
[GRUNTING]

854
01:08:12,150 --> 01:08:14,611
[ARTHUR AND HARRY GRUNTING]

855
01:08:32,963 --> 01:08:36,383
DUMBLEDORE: In the dream,
were you standing next to the victim...

856
01:08:36,550 --> 01:08:38,051
...or looking down at the scene?

857
01:08:38,510 --> 01:08:41,471
Neither. It was like I...

858
01:08:42,055 --> 01:08:44,141
Will you please just tell me
what's happening?

859
01:08:44,349 --> 01:08:46,643
DUMBLEDORE:
Everard, Arthur's on guard duty tonight.

860
01:08:46,852 --> 01:08:49,229
Make sure he's found
by the right people.

861
01:08:49,396 --> 01:08:50,981
HARRY: Sir.
DUMBLEDORE: Phineas.

862
01:08:51,148 --> 01:08:53,442
You must go to your portrait
at Grimmauld Place.

863
01:08:53,608 --> 01:08:56,236
Tell them that Arthur Weasley
is gravely injured...

864
01:08:56,403 --> 01:09:00,574
...and his children will be arriving there
soon by Portkey.

865
01:09:00,741 --> 01:09:03,827
EVERARD: They've got him, Albus.
It was close, but they think he'll make it.

866
01:09:03,994 --> 01:09:06,163
What's more,
the Dark Lord failed to acquire it.

867
01:09:06,371 --> 01:09:07,539
Oh, thank goodness. Next we need to--

868
01:09:07,706 --> 01:09:08,749
[VOLDEMORT WHISPERS]

869
01:09:08,915 --> 01:09:10,167
Look at me!

870
01:09:16,465 --> 01:09:18,675
What's happening to me?

871
01:09:26,558 --> 01:09:28,435
You wished to see me, headmaster?

872
01:09:28,602 --> 01:09:33,523
Oh, Severus. I'm afraid we can't wait.
Not even till the morning.

873
01:09:33,899 --> 01:09:36,818
Otherwise, we'll all be vulnerable.

874
01:09:41,573 --> 01:09:43,200
SNAPE:
It appears there's a connection...

875
01:09:43,408 --> 01:09:45,702
...between the Dark Lord's mind
and your own.

876
01:09:45,911 --> 01:09:50,040
Whether he is, as yet, aware of this
connection is, for the moment, unclear.

877
01:09:50,415 --> 01:09:53,418
Pray he remains ignorant.

878
01:09:53,585 --> 01:09:56,922
You mean, if he knows about it, then...

879
01:09:57,339 --> 01:10:01,718
-...he'll be able to read my mind?
-Read it, control it...

880
01:10:01,927 --> 01:10:03,762
...unhinge it.

881
01:10:03,929 --> 01:10:07,307
In the past, it was often
the Dark Lord's pleasure...

882
01:10:07,474 --> 01:10:09,726
...to invade the minds of his victims...

883
01:10:09,935 --> 01:10:13,480
...creating visions designed
to torture them into madness.

884
01:10:14,606 --> 01:10:19,403
Only after extracting the last exquisite
ounce of agony...

885
01:10:19,569 --> 01:10:23,865
...only when he had them literally
begging for death, would he finally...

886
01:10:24,032 --> 01:10:25,242
...kill them.

887
01:10:26,243 --> 01:10:28,662
Used properly,
the power of Occlumency...

888
01:10:28,829 --> 01:10:32,332
...will help shield you
from access or influence.

889
01:10:32,499 --> 01:10:37,254
In these lessons, I will attempt
to penetrate your mind.

890
01:10:37,838 --> 01:10:40,966
You will attempt to resist.

891
01:10:41,216 --> 01:10:42,676
Prepare yourself.

892
01:10:45,470 --> 01:10:46,638
Legilimens.

893
01:10:54,771 --> 01:10:58,358
Concentrate, Potter. Focus.

894
01:11:17,836 --> 01:11:19,838
[CHILDREN LAUGHING]

895
01:11:24,259 --> 01:11:25,886
SANTA TOY:
Ho, ho, ho. Merry Christmas.

896
01:11:27,095 --> 01:11:29,764
MOLLY:
Here we go.

897
01:11:29,931 --> 01:11:32,100
Daddy's back. Oh.

898
01:11:32,601 --> 01:11:34,603
[MOLLY LAUGHING]

899
01:11:35,270 --> 01:11:38,899
Sit down, everybody, sit down.
That's it. Now, presents.

900
01:11:39,065 --> 01:11:43,445
ARTHUR: And a nice big box for Ron.
MOLLY: Big box for you. And, um...

901
01:11:43,612 --> 01:11:45,530
[STAMMERING]

902
01:11:46,239 --> 01:11:48,450
Fred and George. Come on, open up.

903
01:11:48,617 --> 01:11:50,911
- I want to see your faces.
ARTHUR: Yes.

904
01:11:51,077 --> 01:11:53,497
MOLLY: Try it on.
GINNY: Thanks, Mum. It's perfect.

905
01:11:53,663 --> 01:11:57,959
-Just what he wanted, actually.
-Yeah. Right. Thanks, Mum.

906
01:11:58,126 --> 01:12:01,004
MOLLY: Come on, then, everybody.
Let's clear this away.

907
01:12:01,171 --> 01:12:03,173
Oh, Harry, Harry.

908
01:12:03,340 --> 01:12:05,258
There you are.

909
01:12:06,259 --> 01:12:08,094
-Happy Christmas.
-Thank you.

910
01:12:08,678 --> 01:12:10,514
-Lovely to have you with us.
-Thank you.

911
01:12:10,680 --> 01:12:12,682
MOLLY:
Now, Daddy. Pass that to Daddy.

912
01:12:12,849 --> 01:12:14,559
ARTHUR: Thank you.
MOLLY: Has everybody got?

913
01:12:14,726 --> 01:12:16,102
Fred? George?

914
01:12:16,269 --> 01:12:18,813
-Hermione.
ARTHUR: A Christmas toast.

915
01:12:18,980 --> 01:12:20,857
To Mr. Harry Potter...

916
01:12:21,858 --> 01:12:24,694
...without whom I would not be here.

917
01:12:28,281 --> 01:12:30,617
-Harry.
WEASLEYS: Harry.

918
01:12:30,784 --> 01:12:32,077
Harry.

919
01:12:33,078 --> 01:12:35,622
ARTHUR: That is delicious.
I shall be needing some more of that.

920
01:12:35,789 --> 01:12:38,166
MOLLY:
Daddy, don't forget last Christmas.

921
01:12:39,084 --> 01:12:41,836
I can't understand
why you don't want to wear it, Ronald.

922
01:12:43,296 --> 01:12:45,131
RON:
I look like a bloody idiot, that's why.

923
01:12:45,298 --> 01:12:47,133
HERMIONE:
No more than usual, Ron.

924
01:12:47,342 --> 01:12:49,177
I don't know why...

925
01:12:55,183 --> 01:12:59,771
Nasty brat, standing there
as bold as brass.

926
01:12:59,938 --> 01:13:04,693
Harry Potter,
the boy who stopped the Dark Lord.

927
01:13:04,859 --> 01:13:07,862
Friend of Mudbloods
and blood-traitors alike.

928
01:13:08,280 --> 01:13:10,907
-If my poor mistress only knew...
SIRIUS: Kreacher!

929
01:13:11,116 --> 01:13:13,910
That's enough of your bile.
Away with you!

930
01:13:14,119 --> 01:13:16,079
Of course, master.

931
01:13:16,246 --> 01:13:20,917
Kreacher lives to serve
the noble house of Black.

932
01:13:23,253 --> 01:13:25,130
Sorry about that.

933
01:13:25,714 --> 01:13:29,384
He never was very pleasant,
even when I was a boy.

934
01:13:29,718 --> 01:13:31,803
Not to me, anyway.

935
01:13:32,637 --> 01:13:34,598
What, you grew up here?

936
01:13:34,764 --> 01:13:37,017
SIRIUS:
This is my parents' house.

937
01:13:37,350 --> 01:13:41,187
I offered it to Dumbledore
as headquarters for the Order.

938
01:13:42,314 --> 01:13:45,650
About the only useful thing
I've been able to do.

939
01:13:46,985 --> 01:13:49,362
This is the Black family tree.

940
01:13:50,280 --> 01:13:52,407
My deranged cousin.

941
01:13:52,574 --> 01:13:55,285
I hated the lot of them.

942
01:13:55,452 --> 01:14:00,165
My parents with their pure-blood mania.

943
01:14:03,376 --> 01:14:07,172
My mother did that after I ran away.

944
01:14:09,507 --> 01:14:11,384
Charming woman.

945
01:14:12,677 --> 01:14:14,304
I was 16.

946
01:14:15,180 --> 01:14:16,556
Where did you go?

947
01:14:18,683 --> 01:14:19,893
Round your dad's.

948
01:14:21,394 --> 01:14:23,938
I was always welcome at the Potters'.

949
01:14:24,814 --> 01:14:27,567
I see him so much in you, Harry.

950
01:14:28,193 --> 01:14:30,403
You are so very much alike.

951
01:14:31,321 --> 01:14:33,323
I'm not so sure.

952
01:14:34,366 --> 01:14:35,825
Sirius, when I was...

953
01:14:38,703 --> 01:14:43,208
When I saw Mr. Weasley attacked,
I wasn't just watching.

954
01:14:44,334 --> 01:14:45,835
I was the snake.

955
01:14:46,711 --> 01:14:49,631
And afterwards, in Dumbledore's office...

956
01:14:49,798 --> 01:14:54,010
...there was a moment
when I wanted to--

957
01:14:59,140 --> 01:15:02,018
This connection
between me and Voldemort.

958
01:15:02,727 --> 01:15:06,272
What if the reason for it
is that I am becoming more like him?

959
01:15:07,607 --> 01:15:12,529
I just feel so angry all the time.

960
01:15:12,737 --> 01:15:17,242
And what if, after everything
that I've been through...

961
01:15:17,409 --> 01:15:20,995
...something's gone wrong inside me?
What if I'm becoming bad?

962
01:15:23,623 --> 01:15:26,876
I want you to listen to me
very carefully, Harry.

963
01:15:28,044 --> 01:15:31,047
You're not a bad person.

964
01:15:31,881 --> 01:15:36,261
You're a very good person
who bad things have happened to.

965
01:15:36,845 --> 01:15:37,971
You understand?

966
01:15:40,056 --> 01:15:45,103
Besides, the world isn't split
into good people and Death Eaters.

967
01:15:45,270 --> 01:15:49,774
We've all got both light and dark
inside of us.

968
01:15:50,483 --> 01:15:53,778
What matters
is the part we choose to act on.

969
01:15:55,697 --> 01:15:57,991
That's who we really are.

970
01:15:59,909 --> 01:16:01,578
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

971
01:16:01,786 --> 01:16:03,496
Harry, time to go.

972
01:16:05,290 --> 01:16:09,544
When all this is over,
we'll be a proper family.

973
01:16:09,711 --> 01:16:11,296
You'll see.

974
01:16:12,422 --> 01:16:13,798
Come on.

975
01:16:26,853 --> 01:16:28,688
[VOICES WHISPERING]

976
01:16:51,252 --> 01:16:52,420
Really?

977
01:16:52,587 --> 01:16:55,215
HERMIONE:
Harry. Harry.

978
01:16:55,381 --> 01:16:57,342
Hagrid's back.

979
01:17:00,261 --> 01:17:02,096
I'm sorry.

980
01:17:16,361 --> 01:17:19,489
UMBRIDGE:
I will say this one last time.

981
01:17:19,781 --> 01:17:22,158
I'm ordering you to tell me
where you've been.

982
01:17:22,367 --> 01:17:25,370
HAGRID:
I told you. I've been away for me health.

983
01:17:25,662 --> 01:17:29,833
-Your health?
-Yeah. Bit of fresh air, you know.

984
01:17:29,999 --> 01:17:34,879
Oh, yes. As gamekeeper,
fresh air must be difficult to come by.

985
01:17:36,881 --> 01:17:39,384
If I were you,
I shouldn't get too used to being back.

986
01:17:39,551 --> 01:17:42,887
In fact, I mightn't bother
unpacking at all.

987
01:17:46,766 --> 01:17:49,269
[THUNDER RUMBLING IN THE DISTANCE]

988
01:17:50,895 --> 01:17:52,939
[SNIFFING]

989
01:18:01,781 --> 01:18:04,909
This is top-secret, right?

990
01:18:05,785 --> 01:18:08,162
Dumbledore sent me
to parley with the giants.

991
01:18:08,329 --> 01:18:09,831
-Giants?
HAGRID: Shh.

992
01:18:10,999 --> 01:18:12,041
You found them?

993
01:18:12,208 --> 01:18:16,129
Well, they're not that hard to find, to be
perfectly honest. They're so big, see?

994
01:18:17,005 --> 01:18:20,049
I tried to convince them
to join the cause.

995
01:18:20,216 --> 01:18:22,927
But I wasn't the only one
that was trying to win them over.

996
01:18:23,595 --> 01:18:25,513
-Death Eaters?
HAGRID: Yes.

997
01:18:25,972 --> 01:18:29,309
Trying to persuade them
to join You-Know-Who.

998
01:18:29,809 --> 01:18:32,186
-Did they?
- Igave them Dumbledore's message.

999
01:18:32,353 --> 01:18:36,441
Suppose some of them remember
he was friendly to them. I suppose.

1000
01:18:40,069 --> 01:18:41,362
And they did this to you?

1001
01:18:41,988 --> 01:18:43,031
Not exactly, no.

1002
01:18:43,197 --> 01:18:44,240
[DOG BARKING]

1003
01:18:44,449 --> 01:18:48,244
Oh, go on, you have it, then,
you dozy dog.

1004
01:18:55,376 --> 01:18:57,420
[DOG BARKING]

1005
01:18:57,587 --> 01:18:59,964
[THUNDER RUMBLING IN THE DISTANCE]

1006
01:19:02,216 --> 01:19:04,344
It's changing out there.

1007
01:19:04,761 --> 01:19:06,346
Just like last time.

1008
01:19:07,805 --> 01:19:09,474
There's a storm coming, Harry.

1009
01:19:10,183 --> 01:19:13,269
We'd all best be ready when she does.

1010
01:19:16,689 --> 01:19:18,566
[THUNDER CRASHES]

1011
01:19:37,377 --> 01:19:39,629
[LAUGHING]

1012
01:19:50,264 --> 01:19:53,309
FUDGE: We have confirmed
that 10 high-security prisoners...

1013
01:19:53,518 --> 01:19:56,312
...In the early hours of yesterday evening
did escape.

1014
01:19:56,521 --> 01:20:00,149
And of course, the Muggle prime minister
has been alerted to the danger.

1015
01:20:00,316 --> 01:20:02,402
We strongly suspect...

1016
01:20:03,236 --> 01:20:05,238
...that the breakout was engineered...

1017
01:20:05,405 --> 01:20:09,617
...by a man with personal experience
in escaping from Azkaban...

1018
01:20:09,784 --> 01:20:14,038
...notorious mass murderer Sirius Black...

1019
01:20:15,456 --> 01:20:19,002
...cousin of escapee Bellatrix Lestrange.

1020
01:20:19,168 --> 01:20:21,045
[SCREAMING]

1021
01:20:30,138 --> 01:20:32,432
Dumbledore warned Fudge
this could happen.

1022
01:20:32,598 --> 01:20:35,768
He's gonna get us all killed
just because he can't face the truth.

1023
01:20:35,935 --> 01:20:37,061
SEAMUS:
Harry.

1024
01:20:38,312 --> 01:20:39,564
[, uh...

1025
01:20:40,773 --> 01:20:42,775
I wanted to apologize.

1026
01:20:43,359 --> 01:20:47,530
Now even me mum says the Prophet's
version of things don't add up.

1027
01:20:47,697 --> 01:20:53,619
So, what I'm really trying to say
is that I believe you.

1028
01:21:00,585 --> 01:21:02,170
HARRY:
Neville?

1029
01:21:14,724 --> 01:21:16,893
Fourteen years ago...

1030
01:21:17,101 --> 01:21:21,314
...a Death Eater
named Bellatrix Lestrange...

1031
01:21:21,481 --> 01:21:24,692
...used a Cruciatus Curse on my parents.

1032
01:21:25,234 --> 01:21:29,238
She tortured them for information...

1033
01:21:29,405 --> 01:21:31,616
...but they never gave in.

1034
01:21:33,242 --> 01:21:35,745
I'm quite proud to be their son.

1035
01:21:36,704 --> 01:21:40,625
But I'm not sure
I'm ready for everyone to know just yet.

1036
01:21:46,506 --> 01:21:50,635
We're gonna make them proud, Neville.
That's a promise.

1037
01:21:54,889 --> 01:21:58,601
Make it a powerful memory,
the happiest you can remember.

1038
01:21:58,768 --> 01:22:02,188
Allow it to fill you up.
Keep trying, Seamus.

1039
01:22:02,355 --> 01:22:03,773
George, your turn now.

1040
01:22:05,149 --> 01:22:07,443
Expecto Patronum.

1041
01:22:08,361 --> 01:22:11,781
A full-bodied Patronus
is the most difficult to produce...

1042
01:22:11,948 --> 01:22:15,785
...but shield forms can also be equally
useful against a variety of opponents.

1043
01:22:15,952 --> 01:22:17,203
Wow, that was really good.

1044
01:22:17,912 --> 01:22:19,455
Fantastic, Ginny.

1045
01:22:19,664 --> 01:22:23,668
Remember, your Patronus can only protect
you for as long as you stay focused.

1046
01:22:23,835 --> 01:22:26,170
So focus, Luna.

1047
01:22:29,841 --> 01:22:31,551
Think of the happiest thing you can.

1048
01:22:31,717 --> 01:22:33,678
NEVILLE:
Expecto Patronum.

1049
01:22:33,845 --> 01:22:36,722
-I'm trying.
HARRY: I know. It's good.

1050
01:22:36,889 --> 01:22:39,892
This is really advanced stuff, guys.
You're doing so well.

1051
01:22:40,059 --> 01:22:41,727
[DOG BARKING]
[NEVILLE GRUNTS]

1052
01:22:41,894 --> 01:22:44,313
Expecto Patronum.

1053
01:22:55,408 --> 01:22:56,993
[RUMBLING]

1054
01:23:05,918 --> 01:23:07,712
[POUNDING]

1055
01:23:26,147 --> 01:23:28,733
UMBRIDGE:
I'll make short work of this.

1056
01:23:30,026 --> 01:23:32,028
Bombarda Maxima.

1057
01:23:32,236 --> 01:23:33,946
[RON YELLS]

1058
01:23:50,296 --> 01:23:51,672
Get them.

1059
01:23:52,089 --> 01:23:53,591
UMBRIDGE:
Been watching them for weeks.

1060
01:23:53,758 --> 01:23:55,676
And see, "Dumbledore's Army"...

1061
01:23:56,093 --> 01:23:59,805
...proof of what I've been telling you
right from the beginning, Cornelius.

1062
01:24:01,182 --> 01:24:03,226
All your fear-mongering
about You-Know-Who...

1063
01:24:03,392 --> 01:24:04,936
...never fooled us for a minute.

1064
01:24:05,102 --> 01:24:07,188
We saw your lies for what they were:

1065
01:24:07,355 --> 01:24:11,150
A smokescreen for your bid
to seize control of the Ministry.

1066
01:24:11,317 --> 01:24:12,360
Naturally.

1067
01:24:12,526 --> 01:24:15,071
No, professor.
He had nothing to do with it. It was me.

1068
01:24:15,279 --> 01:24:18,908
Most noble of you, Harry, to shield me,
but as has been pointed out...

1069
01:24:19,075 --> 01:24:23,913
...the parchment clearly says
"Dumbledore"s Army," not "Potter's."

1070
01:24:24,080 --> 01:24:26,707
I instructed Harry
to form this organization.

1071
01:24:26,874 --> 01:24:30,336
And I, and I alone,
am responsible for its activities.

1072
01:24:30,503 --> 01:24:32,338
FUDGE:
Dispatch an owl to the Daily Prophet.

1073
01:24:32,505 --> 01:24:35,049
If we hurry,
we should still make the morning edition.

1074
01:24:35,216 --> 01:24:40,012
Dawlish, Shacklebolt,
you will escort Dumbledore...

1075
01:24:40,179 --> 01:24:41,597
...to Azkaban...

1076
01:24:42,848 --> 01:24:47,436
...to await trial
for conspiracy and sedition.

1077
01:24:47,603 --> 01:24:51,107
Ah. I thought we might hit
this little snag.

1078
01:24:52,316 --> 01:24:55,736
You seem to be laboring
under the delusion that I'm going to--

1079
01:24:56,320 --> 01:24:57,738
What was the phrase?

1080
01:24:57,905 --> 01:24:59,490
--Come quietly.

1081
01:24:59,657 --> 01:25:01,367
Well, I can tell you this:

1082
01:25:01,826 --> 01:25:04,120
I have no intention of going to Azkaban.

1083
01:25:04,328 --> 01:25:05,538
Enough of this.

1084
01:25:06,038 --> 01:25:07,123
Take him.

1085
01:25:08,124 --> 01:25:09,959
[FAWKES SCREECHING]

1086
01:25:10,626 --> 01:25:12,712
[ALL YELL]

1087
01:25:17,967 --> 01:25:19,635
Whoa.

1088
01:25:19,969 --> 01:25:24,348
Well, you may not like him, minister...

1089
01:25:24,515 --> 01:25:26,642
...but you can't deny...

1090
01:25:27,184 --> 01:25:29,937
...Dumbledore has got style.

1091
01:25:35,901 --> 01:25:37,778
[FILCH GRUNTING]

1092
01:25:42,491 --> 01:25:44,493
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

1093
01:25:53,794 --> 01:25:58,674
UMBRIDGE: Boys and girls cannot be
within eight inches of each other.

1094
01:25:58,883 --> 01:26:02,261
Those wishing to join
the Inquisitorial Squad for extra credit...

1095
01:26:02,428 --> 01:26:07,475
Students will be submitted to questioning
about suspected illicit activities.

1096
01:26:07,641 --> 01:26:11,937
Any student in noncompliance
will be expelled.

1097
01:26:16,025 --> 01:26:18,027
[MEN IN PAINTING GRUNTING]

1098
01:26:21,113 --> 01:26:22,907
[YELLING]

1099
01:27:03,614 --> 01:27:05,116
[SIGHS]

1100
01:27:23,134 --> 01:27:24,760
CHO:
Harry.

1101
01:27:31,684 --> 01:27:35,104
RON: You did everything you could.
No one could win against that old hag.

1102
01:27:35,271 --> 01:27:37,606
HERMIONE: Even Dumbledore
didn't see this coming.

1103
01:27:38,524 --> 01:27:40,693
Harry, if it's anyone's fault, it's ours.

1104
01:27:40,860 --> 01:27:42,945
Yeah, we talked you into it.

1105
01:27:43,112 --> 01:27:45,114
Yeah, but I agreed.

1106
01:27:45,656 --> 01:27:49,785
I tried so hard to help,
and all it's done is make things worse.

1107
01:27:51,829 --> 01:27:54,290
Anyway, that doesn't matter anymore.

1108
01:27:55,332 --> 01:27:59,545
Because I don't want to play anymore.
All it does is make you care too much.

1109
01:27:59,712 --> 01:28:02,381
And the more you care,
the more you have to lose.

1110
01:28:02,548 --> 01:28:05,718
-So maybe it's just better to....
-To what?

1111
01:28:08,012 --> 01:28:09,889
To go it alone.

1112
01:28:10,639 --> 01:28:12,224
HAGRID:
Psst.

1113
01:28:16,228 --> 01:28:17,897
Hagrid.

1114
01:28:21,650 --> 01:28:24,069
RON:
Any idea where he's taking us?

1115
01:28:24,236 --> 01:28:27,323
Hagrid, why can't you just tell us?

1116
01:28:29,533 --> 01:28:31,577
[HOOFBEATS APPROACHING]

1117
01:28:31,744 --> 01:28:33,245
[CENTAUR YELLING]

1118
01:28:35,623 --> 01:28:38,292
HAGRID:
I've never seen the centaurs so riled.

1119
01:28:38,459 --> 01:28:41,045
And they're dangerous
at the best of times.

1120
01:28:41,962 --> 01:28:44,298
The Ministry restricts
their territory much more...

1121
01:28:44,465 --> 01:28:46,675
...they'll have a full uprising
on their hands.

1122
01:28:46,842 --> 01:28:48,511
Hagrid, what's going on?

1123
01:28:48,677 --> 01:28:50,888
I'm sorry to be so mysterious, you three.

1124
01:28:51,055 --> 01:28:56,060
I wouldn't be bothering you at all with it,
but with Dumbledore gone...

1125
01:28:56,685 --> 01:28:59,855
...I'll likely be getting the sack
any day now.

1126
01:29:00,064 --> 01:29:03,567
And I just couldn't leave
without telling someone about him.

1127
01:29:07,696 --> 01:29:09,365
Grawpy.

1128
01:29:11,742 --> 01:29:13,869
Down here, you great buffoon.

1129
01:29:19,250 --> 01:29:21,877
Oh, Grawpy.

1130
01:29:22,670 --> 01:29:24,380
Brought you some company.

1131
01:29:36,725 --> 01:29:38,978
HAGRID:
I couldn't just leave him, because--

1132
01:29:39,144 --> 01:29:40,896
Because he's my brother.

1133
01:29:41,105 --> 01:29:42,189
RON:
Blimey.

1134
01:29:42,356 --> 01:29:44,400
HAGRID:
Well, half brother, really.

1135
01:29:44,608 --> 01:29:49,822
He's completely harmless, just like I said.
Little high-spirited, is all.

1136
01:29:50,990 --> 01:29:52,032
[HERMIONE SCREAMS]

1137
01:29:52,199 --> 01:29:54,451
HAGRID: Grawpy, that is not polite.
-Hagrid, do something.

1138
01:29:54,618 --> 01:29:56,870
We talked about this.
You do not grab, do you?

1139
01:29:57,037 --> 01:29:59,290
That's your new friend, Hermione.

1140
01:29:59,456 --> 01:30:00,749
Grawpy.

1141
01:30:00,958 --> 01:30:03,210
[GRAWPY GRUMBLES]
[RON GRUNTS]

1142
01:30:05,129 --> 01:30:06,255
HERMIONE:
Grawp.

1143
01:30:08,299 --> 01:30:11,385
Put me down.

1144
01:30:15,055 --> 01:30:16,640
Now.

1145
01:30:28,777 --> 01:30:29,862
RON:
You all right?

1146
01:30:31,155 --> 01:30:32,823
Fine.

1147
01:30:33,240 --> 01:30:35,534
Just needs a firm hand, is all.

1148
01:30:35,701 --> 01:30:38,162
I think you've got an admirer.

1149
01:30:40,664 --> 01:30:42,791
You just stay away from her, all right?

1150
01:30:47,004 --> 01:30:48,547
[BELL DINGS]

1151
01:31:06,565 --> 01:31:08,108
[DINGING BELL]

1152
01:31:12,905 --> 01:31:15,699
He gets his own food and all.

1153
01:31:16,909 --> 01:31:19,995
It's company he'll be needing
when I'm gone.

1154
01:31:21,330 --> 01:31:23,540
You will look after him, won't you?

1155
01:31:24,041 --> 01:31:26,752
I'm the only family he's got.

1156
01:31:40,349 --> 01:31:42,226
Feeling sentimental?

1157
01:31:45,479 --> 01:31:49,316
-That's private.
-Not to me.

1158
01:31:49,608 --> 01:31:53,112
And not to the Dark Lord,
if you don't improve.

1159
01:31:55,531 --> 01:31:58,701
Every memory he has access to
is a weapon he can use against you.

1160
01:31:58,867 --> 01:32:03,038
You won't last two seconds
if he invades your mind.

1161
01:32:04,248 --> 01:32:06,458
You're just like your father.

1162
01:32:06,625 --> 01:32:08,419
Lazy, arrogant.

1163
01:32:08,585 --> 01:32:10,838
-Don't say a word against my father.
-Weak.

1164
01:32:11,004 --> 01:32:13,173
-I'm not weak.
-Then prove it.

1165
01:32:13,799 --> 01:32:15,718
Control your emotions.

1166
01:32:15,884 --> 01:32:18,846
Discipline your mind.

1167
01:32:21,682 --> 01:32:22,891
Legilimens.

1168
01:32:27,563 --> 01:32:28,897
[ARTHUR GRUNTS]

1169
01:32:30,065 --> 01:32:31,191
VOLDEMORT:
Harry.

1170
01:32:31,358 --> 01:32:33,068
HARRY:
Sirius.

1171
01:32:33,777 --> 01:32:35,070
SNAPE:
I may vomit.

1172
01:32:35,362 --> 01:32:36,405
Stop it.

1173
01:32:37,573 --> 01:32:39,867
Is this what you call control?

1174
01:32:40,367 --> 01:32:43,412
We've been at it for hours.
If I could just rest.

1175
01:32:43,579 --> 01:32:46,999
The Dark Lord isn't resting.

1176
01:32:48,625 --> 01:32:51,962
You and Black, you're two of a kind.
Sentimental children forever whining...

1177
01:32:52,129 --> 01:32:54,673
...about how bitterly unfair
your lives have been.

1178
01:32:54,840 --> 01:32:58,218
Well, it may have escaped your notice,
but life isn't fair.

1179
01:32:58,385 --> 01:33:02,347
Your blessed father knew that.
In fact, he frequently saw to it.

1180
01:33:02,514 --> 01:33:05,559
-My father was a great man.
-Your father was a swine.

1181
01:33:06,602 --> 01:33:08,103
-Legilimens.
-Protego.

1182
01:33:13,650 --> 01:33:15,194
JAMES:
Come on, Moony, Padfoot.

1183
01:33:15,360 --> 01:33:17,446
Snape. Expelliarmus.

1184
01:33:17,613 --> 01:33:19,448
Nice one, James.

1185
01:33:19,823 --> 01:33:22,117
-Dad.
JAMES: Impedimenta.

1186
01:33:22,326 --> 01:33:24,286
ALL [CHANTING]:
Snivellus Greasy. Snivellus Greasy.

1187
01:33:24,453 --> 01:33:27,122
Right. Who wants to see me
take off Snivelly's trousers?

1188
01:33:27,331 --> 01:33:29,541
ALL:
Snivellus Greasy. Snivellus Greasy.

1189
01:33:29,708 --> 01:33:30,918
SNAPE:
Enough.

1190
01:33:32,878 --> 01:33:34,463
Enough.

1191
01:33:42,971 --> 01:33:45,599
Your lessons are at an end.

1192
01:33:45,766 --> 01:33:46,892
I——

1193
01:33:47,059 --> 01:33:50,354
Get out.

1194
01:34:04,284 --> 01:34:06,453
[BOY CRYING]

1195
01:34:07,538 --> 01:34:09,706
FRED: What's your name?
BOY: Michael.

1196
01:34:09,873 --> 01:34:11,792
FRED:
Your hand's gonna be fine, Michael.

1197
01:34:11,959 --> 01:34:15,003
GEORGE:
Yeah. It's not as bad as it seems. See?

1198
01:34:15,170 --> 01:34:17,172
It's fading already.

1199
01:34:17,381 --> 01:34:22,094
You can hardly see ours anymore,
and the pain stops after a while.

1200
01:34:23,428 --> 01:34:25,430
[UMBRIDGE CLEARS THROAT]

1201
01:34:29,476 --> 01:34:32,187
UMBRIDGE:
As I told you once before, Mr. Potter...

1202
01:34:32,396 --> 01:34:36,149
...naughty children
deserve to be punished.

1203
01:34:39,194 --> 01:34:40,529
FRED:
You know, George...

1204
01:34:40,696 --> 01:34:44,366
...I've always felt our futures lay outside
the world of academic achievement.

1205
01:34:44,533 --> 01:34:49,121
Fred, I've been thinking
exactly the same thing.

1206
01:35:10,434 --> 01:35:11,852
[DISTANT BANGING]

1207
01:35:45,093 --> 01:35:47,346
[FIREWORKS EXPLODING
AND WHISTLING]

1208
01:36:01,068 --> 01:36:02,736
FRED:
All right, professor!

1209
01:36:03,236 --> 01:36:05,197
[FRED AND GEORGE LAUGHING]

1210
01:36:05,364 --> 01:36:07,366
[STUDENTS CHEERING]

1211
01:36:11,495 --> 01:36:13,288
Here you go.

1212
01:36:21,546 --> 01:36:23,256
[UMBRIDGE YELPS]

1213
01:36:25,342 --> 01:36:26,802
Aah!

1214
01:36:28,136 --> 01:36:29,888
[CRABBE WHIMPERS AND YELPS]

1215
01:36:30,806 --> 01:36:32,349
[MALFOY YELPS]

1216
01:36:38,230 --> 01:36:40,065
Ready when you are.

1217
01:36:43,527 --> 01:36:45,445
[GROWLING]

1218
01:36:48,907 --> 01:36:50,909
[UMBRIDGE YELLING]

1219
01:37:11,847 --> 01:37:13,432
[UMBRIDGE SCREAMS]

1220
01:37:14,057 --> 01:37:16,351
[STUDENTS CHEERING]

1221
01:37:17,602 --> 01:37:20,397
[FRED AND GEORGE LAUGHING
AND WHOOPING]

1222
01:38:05,817 --> 01:38:09,071
VOLDEMORT:
I need that prophecy.

1223
01:38:09,237 --> 01:38:11,114
SIRIUS:
You'll have to kill me.

1224
01:38:11,907 --> 01:38:16,495
Oh, I will.
But first, you will fetch it for me.

1225
01:38:16,661 --> 01:38:18,371
-Crucio.
-Aah!

1226
01:38:20,916 --> 01:38:23,251
-Crucio.
-Aah!

1227
01:38:26,838 --> 01:38:28,507
[SIRIUS YELLING]

1228
01:38:34,054 --> 01:38:35,514
Sirius.

1229
01:38:35,680 --> 01:38:36,848
HERMIONE:
Harry, are you sure?

1230
01:38:37,015 --> 01:38:39,309
HARRY:
I saw it. It's just like with Mr. Weasley.

1231
01:38:39,476 --> 01:38:41,353
It's the door I've been dreaming about.

1232
01:38:41,520 --> 01:38:43,605
I couldn't remember
where I'd seen it before.

1233
01:38:43,772 --> 01:38:45,690
Sirius said Voldemort
was after something.

1234
01:38:45,857 --> 01:38:49,152
Something he didn't have the last time,
in the Department of Mysteries.

1235
01:38:49,319 --> 01:38:51,279
Harry, please, just listen.

1236
01:38:52,781 --> 01:38:54,783
What if Voldemort
meant for you to see this?

1237
01:38:56,076 --> 01:38:59,204
What if he's only hurting Sirius
because he's trying to get to you?

1238
01:38:59,371 --> 01:39:02,874
What if he is?
I'm supposed to just let him die?

1239
01:39:03,041 --> 01:39:06,545
Hermione,
he's the only family I've got left.

1240
01:39:09,089 --> 01:39:10,173
What do we do?

1241
01:39:11,508 --> 01:39:13,135
HARRY:
We'll have to use the Floo Network.

1242
01:39:13,301 --> 01:39:15,470
HERMIONE: Umbridge has the chimneys
under surveillance.

1243
01:39:15,679 --> 01:39:17,180
HARRY:
Not all of them.

1244
01:39:19,975 --> 01:39:21,309
HARRY:
Alohomora.

1245
01:39:23,103 --> 01:39:25,188
[CATS MEWLING]

1246
01:39:32,529 --> 01:39:34,197
Alert the Order if you can.

1247
01:39:34,364 --> 01:39:36,032
RON:
Are you mental? We're going with you.

1248
01:39:36,199 --> 01:39:37,993
It's too dangerous.

1249
01:39:38,201 --> 01:39:41,788
When are you going to get it
into your head? We're in this together.

1250
01:39:41,955 --> 01:39:45,167
That you are.

1251
01:39:45,333 --> 01:39:48,211
Caught this one
trying to help the Weasley girl.

1252
01:39:53,216 --> 01:39:55,343
You were going to Dumbledore,
weren't you?

1253
01:39:55,510 --> 01:39:57,512
-Liar.

1254
01:39:57,721 --> 01:40:00,515
SNAPE: You sent for me, headmistress?
-Snape, yes.

1255
01:40:00,724 --> 01:40:04,227
The time has come for answers, whether
he wants to give them to me or not.

1256
01:40:04,603 --> 01:40:06,146
Have you brought the Veritaserum?

1257
01:40:06,313 --> 01:40:09,191
I'm afraid you've used up
all my stores interrogating students.

1258
01:40:09,357 --> 01:40:12,527
The last of it on Miss Chang.

1259
01:40:16,573 --> 01:40:18,033
Unless you wish to poison him--

1260
01:40:18,241 --> 01:40:22,662
And I assure you, I would have
the greatest sympathy if you did.

1261
01:40:23,246 --> 01:40:25,248
--I cannot help you.

1262
01:40:27,626 --> 01:40:29,336
HARRY:
He's got Padfoot.

1263
01:40:30,378 --> 01:40:33,882
He's got Padfoot at the place
where it's hidden.

1264
01:40:34,341 --> 01:40:36,468
Padfoot? What is Padfoot?
Where what is hidden?

1265
01:40:36,635 --> 01:40:38,178
What is he talking about, Snape?

1266
01:40:44,851 --> 01:40:46,853
No idea.

1267
01:40:51,358 --> 01:40:52,901
Very well.

1268
01:40:53,902 --> 01:40:56,279
You give me no choice, Potter.

1269
01:40:56,613 --> 01:40:59,574
As this is an issue of Ministry security...

1270
01:40:59,783 --> 01:41:01,826
...you leave me with...

1271
01:41:02,577 --> 01:41:04,537
...no alternative.

1272
01:41:05,330 --> 01:41:07,540
The Cruciatus Curse
ought to loosen your tongue.

1273
01:41:07,707 --> 01:41:09,167
That's illegal.

1274
01:41:09,334 --> 01:41:12,295
What Cornelius doesn't know
won't hurt him.

1275
01:41:19,803 --> 01:41:21,304
Tell her, Harry!

1276
01:41:22,806 --> 01:41:24,224
Tell me what?

1277
01:41:25,433 --> 01:41:27,435
Well, if you won't tell her where it is...

1278
01:41:28,103 --> 01:41:29,854
I will.

1279
01:41:31,481 --> 01:41:33,316
Where what is?

1280
01:41:34,484 --> 01:41:36,820
Dumbledore's secret weapon.

1281
01:41:41,825 --> 01:41:43,326
How much further?

1282
01:41:43,493 --> 01:41:45,161
Not far.

1283
01:41:47,163 --> 01:41:50,875
It had to be somewhere
students wouldn't find it accidentally.

1284
01:41:55,213 --> 01:41:56,673
[WHISPERS]
What are you doing?

1285
01:41:56,840 --> 01:41:58,633
[WHISPERS]
Improvising.

1286
01:42:07,142 --> 01:42:08,768
UMBRIDGE:
Well?

1287
01:42:10,061 --> 01:42:12,188
Where is this weapon?

1288
01:42:17,110 --> 01:42:19,362
There isn't one, is there?

1289
01:42:22,157 --> 01:42:24,367
You were trying to trick me.

1290
01:42:28,496 --> 01:42:30,081
You know...

1291
01:42:31,499 --> 01:42:33,501
...| really hate children.

1292
01:42:35,211 --> 01:42:36,421
[RUSTLING]

1293
01:42:36,588 --> 01:42:37,964
[UMBRIDGE GASPS]

1294
01:42:49,100 --> 01:42:53,521
You have no business here, centaur.
This is a Ministry matter.

1295
01:42:56,191 --> 01:42:57,859
Lower your weapons.

1296
01:42:58,026 --> 01:43:03,573
I warn you, under the law,
as creatures of near-human intelligence...

1297
01:43:03,740 --> 01:43:04,991
Protego.

1298
01:43:05,241 --> 01:43:06,409
How dare you?

1299
01:43:07,035 --> 01:43:08,536
Filthy half-breed.

1300
01:43:09,287 --> 01:43:10,330
Incarcerous.

1301
01:43:10,705 --> 01:43:12,665
[CENTAUR GASPS]

1302
01:43:14,959 --> 01:43:16,920
[CENTAUR CHOKING]

1303
01:43:23,551 --> 01:43:26,137
Please. Please stop it. Please.

1304
01:43:26,304 --> 01:43:30,975
Now, enough. I will have order.

1305
01:43:32,435 --> 01:43:34,062
[UMBRIDGE SCREAMS]

1306
01:43:35,980 --> 01:43:37,440
[CENTAURS YELLING]

1307
01:43:39,818 --> 01:43:42,404
UMBRIDGE:
You filthy animal.

1308
01:43:42,570 --> 01:43:45,532
Do you know who I am?

1309
01:43:45,698 --> 01:43:48,535
Leave him alone. It's not his fault.

1310
01:43:48,701 --> 01:43:50,578
No, he doesn't understand.

1311
01:43:54,874 --> 01:43:56,709
[UMBRIDGE YELPS]

1312
01:43:58,253 --> 01:44:01,714
Potter, do something.
Tell them I mean no harm.

1313
01:44:01,881 --> 01:44:03,800
I'm sorry, professor.

1314
01:44:03,967 --> 01:44:06,928
- But I must not tell lies.
- What are you doing?

1315
01:44:07,095 --> 01:44:10,974
I am Senior Undersecretary
Dolores Jane Umbridge.

1316
01:44:11,474 --> 01:44:13,601
Let me go!

1317
01:44:13,893 --> 01:44:15,645
[UMBRIDGE SCREAMING]

1318
01:44:16,271 --> 01:44:18,106
HERMIONE:
Thank you, Grawp.

1319
01:44:18,273 --> 01:44:21,776
HARRY:
Hermione. Hermione, Sirius.

1320
01:44:30,034 --> 01:44:33,621
-How'd you get away?
-Puking Pastilles. It wasn't pretty.

1321
01:44:33,788 --> 01:44:35,915
Told them I was hungry,
wanted some sweets.

1322
01:44:36,082 --> 01:44:38,626
They told me to bugger off
and ate the lot themselves.

1323
01:44:39,502 --> 01:44:41,004
That was clever, Ron.

1324
01:44:41,796 --> 01:44:44,299
-Has been known to happen.
-It was brilliant.

1325
01:44:44,507 --> 01:44:46,301
So how are we getting to London?

1326
01:44:47,635 --> 01:44:51,181
Look, it's not that I don't appreciate
everything you've done, all of you...

1327
01:44:52,015 --> 01:44:54,726
...but I've got you
into enough trouble as it is.

1328
01:44:54,893 --> 01:44:57,854
Dumbledore's Army's supposed to be
about doing something real.

1329
01:44:58,188 --> 01:45:00,315
Or was that all just words to you?

1330
01:45:02,192 --> 01:45:05,403
Maybe you don't have to do this
all by yourself, mate.

1331
01:45:10,325 --> 01:45:12,535
So how are we going to get to London?

1332
01:45:13,870 --> 01:45:16,122
We fly, of course.

1333
01:45:22,045 --> 01:45:24,172
[THESTRAL WAILS]

1334
01:45:40,980 --> 01:45:43,107
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

1335
01:45:45,443 --> 01:45:47,695
[THESTRAL WAILING]

1336
01:46:03,753 --> 01:46:05,380
[ELEVATOR DINGS]

1337
01:46:07,173 --> 01:46:09,342
WOMAN'S VOICE:
Department of Mysteries.

1338
01:46:18,184 --> 01:46:19,894
This is it.

1339
01:46:56,639 --> 01:46:58,474
[DOOR OPENING]

1340
01:47:12,864 --> 01:47:15,199
HARRY:
Ninety-two. Ninety-three.

1341
01:47:16,909 --> 01:47:18,286
Ninety-four.

1342
01:47:19,537 --> 01:47:20,580
Ninety-five.

1343
01:47:33,176 --> 01:47:35,887
-He should be here.
NEVILLE: Harry.

1344
01:47:38,598 --> 01:47:39,891
It's got your name on it.

1345
01:48:05,083 --> 01:48:09,462
TRELAWNEY: The one with the power
to vanquish the Dark Lord approaches.

1346
01:48:10,296 --> 01:48:12,715
And the Dark Lord
shall mark him as his equal...

1347
01:48:12,882 --> 01:48:15,718
...but he shall have power
the Dark Lord knows not.

1348
01:48:21,349 --> 01:48:26,729
For neither can live
while the other survives.

1349
01:48:29,232 --> 01:48:30,316
HERMIONE:
Harry.

1350
01:48:40,785 --> 01:48:42,286
HARRY:
Where's Sirius?

1351
01:48:42,453 --> 01:48:47,542
MAN: You know, you really should learn
to tell the difference between dreams...

1352
01:48:50,461 --> 01:48:52,630
...and reality.

1353
01:48:53,881 --> 01:48:58,845
You saw only what the Dark Lord
wanted you to see.

1354
01:48:59,554 --> 01:49:01,055
Now, hand me the prophecy.

1355
01:49:01,264 --> 01:49:03,307
If you do anything to us, I'll break it.

1356
01:49:03,516 --> 01:49:05,560
[LESTRANGE LAUGHING]

1357
01:49:06,060 --> 01:49:08,646
LESTRANGE:
He knows how to play.

1358
01:49:08,813 --> 01:49:12,608
Itty, bitty baby.

1359
01:49:12,775 --> 01:49:14,026
Potter.

1360
01:49:14,569 --> 01:49:16,446
Bellatrix Lestrange.

1361
01:49:16,612 --> 01:49:19,574
Neville Longbottom, is it?
How's Mum and Dad?

1362
01:49:19,782 --> 01:49:21,576
Better, now they're about to be avenged.

1363
01:49:24,412 --> 01:49:29,292
Now, let's everybody just calm down...

1364
01:49:29,709 --> 01:49:31,210
...shall we?

1365
01:49:31,377 --> 01:49:33,838
All we want is that prophecy.

1366
01:49:34,005 --> 01:49:36,048
Why did Voldemort
need me to come and get this?

1367
01:49:36,215 --> 01:49:38,009
LESTRANGE [WHISPERS]:
You dare speak his name?

1368
01:49:39,552 --> 01:49:41,137
You filthy half-blood!

1369
01:49:41,304 --> 01:49:43,931
It's all right.
He's just a curious lad, aren't you?

1370
01:49:45,850 --> 01:49:51,314
Prophecies can only be retrieved
by those about whom they are made.

1371
01:49:51,481 --> 01:49:54,233
Which is lucky for you, really.

1372
01:49:57,987 --> 01:49:59,947
Haven't you always wondered...

1373
01:50:00,448 --> 01:50:05,620
...what was the reason for the connection
between you and the Dark Lord?

1374
01:50:06,370 --> 01:50:08,873
Why he was unable to kill you...

1375
01:50:09,040 --> 01:50:11,584
...when you were just an infant?

1376
01:50:12,960 --> 01:50:17,757
Don't you want to know
the secret of your scar?

1377
01:50:18,674 --> 01:50:23,095
All the answers are there, Potter,
in your hand.

1378
01:50:24,347 --> 01:50:26,349
All you have to do...

1379
01:50:26,849 --> 01:50:28,851
...Is give it to me.

1380
01:50:29,101 --> 01:50:32,396
Then I can show you everything.

1381
01:50:41,155 --> 01:50:42,949
HARRY:
I've waited 14 years.

1382
01:50:43,533 --> 01:50:44,867
I know.

1383
01:50:46,160 --> 01:50:49,080
I guess I can wait a little longer.
Now. Stupefy.

1384
01:50:49,247 --> 01:50:50,665
STUDENTS:
Stupefy.

1385
01:51:06,806 --> 01:51:07,890
Levicorpus.

1386
01:51:14,397 --> 01:51:16,399
NEVILLE:
Petrificus Totalus.

1387
01:51:16,566 --> 01:51:18,401
Well done, Neville.

1388
01:51:23,072 --> 01:51:24,115
[HERMIONE GASPS]

1389
01:51:26,826 --> 01:51:28,411
Stupefy.

1390
01:51:30,121 --> 01:51:31,414
-Stupefy.
-Stupefy.

1391
01:51:42,508 --> 01:51:44,427
Stupefy.

1392
01:51:46,095 --> 01:51:48,055
[GINNY SCREAMS]
[NEVILLE AND RON GRUNT]

1393
01:51:48,264 --> 01:51:49,515
[ALL PANTING]

1394
01:51:51,934 --> 01:51:54,228
Reducto.

1395
01:52:10,244 --> 01:52:12,371
HARRY:
Get back to the door.

1396
01:52:28,512 --> 01:52:30,348
[ALL SHOUTING]

1397
01:52:35,478 --> 01:52:37,480
[ALL GRUNT]

1398
01:52:47,657 --> 01:52:52,161
Department of Mysteries.
They got that bit right, didn't they?

1399
01:52:53,204 --> 01:52:55,206
[VOICES WHISPERING]

1400
01:52:57,375 --> 01:52:59,293
HARRY:
The voices.

1401
01:52:59,835 --> 01:53:01,879
Can you tell what they're saying?

1402
01:53:03,547 --> 01:53:05,716
There aren't any voices, Harry.

1403
01:53:06,509 --> 01:53:08,219
Let's get out of here.

1404
01:53:08,386 --> 01:53:10,012
I hear them too.

1405
01:53:13,099 --> 01:53:15,726
HERMIONE:
Harry, it's just an empty archway.

1406
01:53:18,521 --> 01:53:19,897
Please, Harry.

1407
01:53:20,648 --> 01:53:22,525
Get behind me.

1408
01:53:28,948 --> 01:53:30,825
[ALL GRUNTING]

1409
01:54:02,106 --> 01:54:03,774
[HERMIONE WHIMPERING]

1410
01:54:04,775 --> 01:54:07,194
[LUCIUS CHUCKLING]

1411
01:54:09,071 --> 01:54:11,782
Did you actually believe...

1412
01:54:11,949 --> 01:54:16,579
...or were you truly naive enough
to think...

1413
01:54:17,163 --> 01:54:22,293
...that children stood a chance
against us?

1414
01:54:25,796 --> 01:54:29,592
I'll make this simple for you, Potter.

1415
01:54:33,220 --> 01:54:36,557
Give me the prophecy now...

1416
01:54:36,724 --> 01:54:40,728
...or watch your friends die.

1417
01:54:53,657 --> 01:54:55,117
-Don't give it to him, Harry.
-Shh!

1418
01:55:21,352 --> 01:55:24,105
Get away from my godson.

1419
01:55:24,271 --> 01:55:25,648
[LUCIUS GRUNTS]

1420
01:55:44,667 --> 01:55:46,418
[DEATH EATER GRUNTING]

1421
01:55:54,218 --> 01:55:56,804
Now, listen to me.
Take the others and get out of here.

1422
01:55:57,179 --> 01:55:58,973
What? No, I'm staying with you.

1423
01:55:59,181 --> 01:56:01,976
You've done beautifully.

1424
01:56:02,685 --> 01:56:04,270
Now, let me take it from here.

1425
01:56:04,436 --> 01:56:05,479
LUCIUS:
Black.

1426
01:56:11,610 --> 01:56:13,279
[SIRIUS GRUNTING]

1427
01:56:17,449 --> 01:56:19,451
[LESTRANGE LAUGHING]

1428
01:56:20,619 --> 01:56:22,121
[ALL GRUNTING]

1429
01:56:24,748 --> 01:56:26,584
[LESTRANGE LAUGHING]

1430
01:56:32,631 --> 01:56:33,966
Expelliarmus!

1431
01:56:34,133 --> 01:56:35,467
Nice one, James.

1432
01:56:38,721 --> 01:56:40,055
[LUCIUS GRUNTS]

1433
01:56:42,725 --> 01:56:44,226
LESTRANGE:
Avada Kedavra.

1434
01:56:45,060 --> 01:56:46,562
[SIRIUS GROANS]

1435
01:57:04,371 --> 01:57:06,749
[MUTED SOUND]
No. No.

1436
01:57:19,762 --> 01:57:21,513
[LESTRANGE CHUCKLES]

1437
01:57:30,773 --> 01:57:33,317
LESTRANGE:
I killed Sirius Black. Ha-ha-ha!

1438
01:57:34,276 --> 01:57:36,278
-You coming to get me?
-Crucio.

1439
01:57:36,654 --> 01:57:39,114
[LESTRANGE SCREAMS AND WHIMPERS]

1440
01:57:40,366 --> 01:57:42,284
[LESTRANGE GASPS]

1441
01:57:48,582 --> 01:57:51,752
VOLDEMORT:
You've got to mean it, Harry.

1442
01:57:51,919 --> 01:57:55,673
She killed him. She deserves it.

1443
01:57:59,510 --> 01:58:02,721
You know the spell, Harry.

1444
01:58:10,688 --> 01:58:12,815
[LESTRANGE GIGGLING]

1445
01:58:14,316 --> 01:58:15,901
Do it.

1446
01:58:17,903 --> 01:58:19,989
[VOLDEMORT GRUNTS]
[WAND CLATTERS]

1447
01:58:23,575 --> 01:58:26,537
VOLDEMORT:
So weak.

1448
01:58:33,335 --> 01:58:36,505
It was foolish of you
to come here tonight, Tom.

1449
01:58:36,672 --> 01:58:38,424
The Aurors are on their way.

1450
01:58:38,590 --> 01:58:42,845
By which time I shall be gone, and you...

1451
01:58:44,346 --> 01:58:46,432
...shall be dead.

1452
01:58:51,979 --> 01:58:53,564
[VOLDEMORT YELLING]

1453
01:58:58,360 --> 01:58:59,903
[VOLDEMORT GRUNTING]

1454
01:59:04,992 --> 01:59:06,368
[HARRY GRUNTING]

1455
01:59:18,881 --> 01:59:20,299
[VOLDEMORT LAUGHING]

1456
01:59:21,008 --> 01:59:22,551
[HISSING]

1457
01:59:38,400 --> 01:59:40,235
[VOLDEMORT GRUNTING]

1458
01:59:50,537 --> 01:59:51,997
[VOLDEMORT YELLS]

1459
01:59:58,212 --> 01:59:59,922
[SCREAMS]

1460
02:00:47,886 --> 02:00:49,388
[HARRY GASPS]

1461
02:00:50,764 --> 02:00:52,224
[HARRY GRUNTS]

1462
02:01:00,732 --> 02:01:02,609
[IN DISTORTED VOICE]
You've lost, old man.

1463
02:01:04,987 --> 02:01:05,988
[HARRY SCREAMS]

1464
02:01:06,155 --> 02:01:07,906
[LILY SCREAMS]

1465
02:01:14,997 --> 02:01:16,874
[HARRY GRUNTING AND PANTING]

1466
02:01:22,754 --> 02:01:23,797
Harry.

1467
02:01:24,590 --> 02:01:25,632
Aah!

1468
02:01:27,926 --> 02:01:29,428
VOLDEMORT:
So weak.

1469
02:01:29,928 --> 02:01:32,139
So vulnerable.

1470
02:01:36,435 --> 02:01:37,519
Look at me.

1471
02:01:40,022 --> 02:01:44,234
Harry, it isn't how you are alike.

1472
02:01:44,401 --> 02:01:46,904
It's how you are not.

1473
02:01:47,863 --> 02:01:49,031
Aah!

1474
02:01:51,825 --> 02:01:53,327
Harry?

1475
02:02:10,844 --> 02:02:11,970
[GRUNTS]

1476
02:02:20,395 --> 02:02:21,897
[HERMIONE LAUGHING]

1477
02:02:25,734 --> 02:02:27,194
You're the weak one...

1478
02:02:27,819 --> 02:02:31,949
...and you'll never know
love or friendship.

1479
02:02:35,369 --> 02:02:38,247
And I feel sorry for you.

1480
02:02:47,339 --> 02:02:48,757
[VOLDEMORT SCREAMS]

1481
02:03:01,311 --> 02:03:04,773
You're a fool, Harry Potter.

1482
02:03:05,732 --> 02:03:10,862
And you will lose everything.

1483
02:03:12,239 --> 02:03:13,991
[WHOOSHING]

1484
02:03:25,794 --> 02:03:27,462
He's back.

1485
02:03:46,481 --> 02:03:48,317
[FLASHBULBS POPPING]

1486
02:04:35,197 --> 02:04:36,865
I know how you feel, Harry.

1487
02:04:37,032 --> 02:04:38,700
No, you don't.

1488
02:04:44,289 --> 02:04:45,666
It's my fault.

1489
02:04:45,832 --> 02:04:49,127
No, the fault is mine.

1490
02:04:50,128 --> 02:04:51,880
I knew it was only a matter of time...

1491
02:04:52,047 --> 02:04:55,133
...before Voldemort made the connection
between you.

1492
02:04:55,926 --> 02:05:00,180
I thought by distancing myself from you,
as I have done all year...

1493
02:05:00,347 --> 02:05:05,602
...he'd be less tempted, and therefore
you might be more protected.

1494
02:05:08,397 --> 02:05:11,733
The prophecy said:

1495
02:05:12,359 --> 02:05:16,321
"Neither one can live
while the other one survives."

1496
02:05:17,656 --> 02:05:23,745
It means one of us
is gonna have to kill the other, in the end.

1497
02:05:25,747 --> 02:05:27,290
Yes.

1498
02:05:27,749 --> 02:05:29,334
Why didn't you tell me?

1499
02:05:29,501 --> 02:05:33,088
For the same reason
you tried to save Sirius.

1500
02:05:33,255 --> 02:05:35,757
The same reason your friends saved you.

1501
02:05:36,550 --> 02:05:40,053
After all these years,
after all you've suffered...

1502
02:05:40,262 --> 02:05:43,140
...I didn't want to cause you
any more pain.

1503
02:05:44,599 --> 02:05:46,768
I cared too much about you.

1504
02:06:11,585 --> 02:06:13,920
How come you're not at the feast?

1505
02:06:14,087 --> 02:06:18,633
Lost all my possessions.
Apparently people have been hiding them.

1506
02:06:18,800 --> 02:06:21,887
- That's awful.
- Oh, it's all good fun.

1507
02:06:22,053 --> 02:06:25,515
But as it's the last night,
I really do need them back.

1508
02:06:25,682 --> 02:06:28,059
Do you want any help finding them?

1509
02:06:30,937 --> 02:06:34,149
I'm sorry about your godfather, Harry.

1510
02:06:41,198 --> 02:06:43,283
Are you sure you don't want
any help looking?

1511
02:06:43,450 --> 02:06:45,118
That's all right.

1512
02:06:45,327 --> 02:06:47,454
Anyway, my mum always said...

1513
02:06:47,621 --> 02:06:51,458
...the things we lose have a way
of coming back to us in the end.

1514
02:06:54,711 --> 02:06:57,964
If not always in the way we expect.

1515
02:06:59,466 --> 02:07:02,177
Think I'll just go have some pudding.

1516
02:07:13,355 --> 02:07:15,524
[TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWING]

1517
02:07:37,879 --> 02:07:40,757
I've been thinking about something
Dumbledore said to me.

1518
02:07:40,924 --> 02:07:42,634
What's that?

1519
02:07:43,218 --> 02:07:46,012
That even though
we've got a fight ahead of us...

1520
02:07:46,179 --> 02:07:49,266
...we've got one thing
that Voldemort doesn't have.

1521
02:07:49,432 --> 02:07:50,934
Yeah?

1522
02:07:52,894 --> 02:07:55,188
Something worth fighting for.

1523
02:18:10,178 --> 02:18:12,180
[English - US - SDH]
